altering the animal species, as

00:04:42.950 --> 00:04:45.750 align:middle line:84%
well as ourselves, all
of these are influential

00:04:45.750 --> 00:04:47.607 align:middle line:84%
and yet we sort of
turn our eyes to them

00:04:47.607 --> 00:04:48.690 align:middle line:90%
and not really look at it.

00:04:48.690 --> 00:04:51.050 align:middle line:84%
And the fact is, science
is sort of saying,

00:04:51.050 --> 00:04:54.230 align:middle line:84%
it's time to open up your
eyes because we are really

00:04:54.230 --> 00:04:56.570 align:middle line:84%
treading on very
dangerous territory.

00:04:56.570 --> 00:04:59.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So opening up our eyes,
meaning our inner environment

00:04:59.670 --> 00:05:01.385 align:middle line:84%
as well as our
outer environment.

00:05:01.385 --> 00:05:02.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Yeah.

00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:03.593 align:middle line:84%
This is, for me,
it's very interesting

00:05:03.593 --> 00:05:06.220 align:middle line:84%
because my work, which I
published in my first book

00:05:06.220 --> 00:05:09.020 align:middle line:84%
called "The Biology of
Belief" really talked

00:05:09.020 --> 00:05:12.020 align:middle line:84%
about how our beliefs
control our personal biology

00:05:12.020 --> 00:05:13.532 align:middle line:90%
and the life that we experience.

00:05:13.532 --> 00:05:14.990 align:middle line:84%
And in writing that
book, I started

00:05:14.990 --> 00:05:16.323 align:middle line:90%
to recognize, I said well, wait.

00:05:16.323 --> 00:05:19.460 align:middle line:84%
If we personally
create our own lives,

00:05:19.460 --> 00:05:22.680 align:middle line:84%
what is the consequence when
thousands or millions of people

00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:24.410 align:middle line:90%
share the exact same belief.

00:05:24.410 --> 00:05:26.410 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden I
said, yes, that's what

00:05:26.410 --> 00:05:28.380 align:middle line:84%
manifests the reality
that we're in.

00:05:28.380 --> 00:05:30.890 align:middle line:84%
So when culture changes
its belief system,

00:05:30.890 --> 00:05:32.982 align:middle line:84%
then the cultures
change as well.

00:05:32.982 --> 00:05:34.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's why you
talk about, specifically

00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:39.110 align:middle line:84%
on the cellular level, how
it grows and how it dies

00:05:39.110 --> 00:05:42.140 align:middle line:84%
and how it moves towards
growth in a positive state,

00:05:42.140 --> 00:05:43.860 align:middle line:84%
and then it goes
towards degeneration

00:05:43.860 --> 00:05:44.895 align:middle line:90%
in a negative state.

00:05:44.895 --> 00:05:46.770 align:middle line:84%
That's basically what
our planet does, right?

00:05:46.770 --> 00:05:49.061 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: It's exactly facing
that situation right now.

00:05:49.061 --> 00:05:51.390 align:middle line:84%
And it's very interesting
because Mother Nature

00:05:51.390 --> 00:05:54.200 align:middle line:84%
is a wonderful gardener,
takes care of this garden.

00:05:54.200 --> 00:05:56.930 align:middle line:84%
And then what she
will do is remove

00:05:56.930 --> 00:05:59.295 align:middle line:84%
what we would call
pests from the garden.

00:05:59.295 --> 00:06:00.920 align:middle line:84%
Anything that gets
into the garden that

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:03.530 align:middle line:84%
destroys the harmony
of the environment,

00:06:03.530 --> 00:06:06.210 align:middle line:84%
nature will ultimately
eliminate and those things

00:06:06.210 --> 00:06:07.480 align:middle line:90%
will go extinct.

00:06:07.480 --> 00:06:09.170 align:middle line:84%
And, unfortunately,
at this moment,

00:06:09.170 --> 00:06:11.820 align:middle line:90%
we really-- we are those pests.

00:06:11.820 --> 00:06:14.519 align:middle line:84%
Human civilization is
undermining the garden.

00:06:14.519 --> 00:06:16.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I don't think
that we need to be removed,

00:06:16.810 --> 00:06:17.910 align:middle line:90%
so what are the options?

00:06:17.910 --> 00:06:19.980 align:middle line:84%
What is the choice
at this point?

00:06:19.980 --> 00:06:23.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, the choice is
to recognize how we are actually

00:06:23.290 --> 00:06:28.810 align:middle line:84%
influencing the world and owning
the reality of human power

00:06:28.810 --> 00:06:31.276 align:middle line:84%
in altering the state
of the environment.

00:06:31.276 --> 00:06:32.900 align:middle line:84%
So we have to own
that we are involved.

00:06:32.900 --> 00:06:35.760 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people think oh, well,
humans can't change the Earth.

00:06:35.760 --> 00:06:39.025 align:middle line:84%
And it's like oh, my god,
yes we can and we are.

00:06:39.025 --> 00:06:40.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But how?

00:06:40.040 --> 00:06:41.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: We're changing
it so profoundly.

00:06:41.790 --> 00:06:46.950 align:middle line:84%
I mean I remember when I went
to school I studied the three

00:06:46.950 --> 00:06:50.942 align:middle line:84%
seas in middle Europe, and they
were the ABC, the Aral Sea,

00:06:50.942 --> 00:06:52.400 align:middle line:84%
the Black Sea, and
the Caspian Sea.

00:06:52.400 --> 00:06:52.880 align:middle line:90%
Sea.

00:06:52.880 --> 00:06:54.713 align:middle line:84%
I remember how easy it
was to remember that.

00:06:54.713 --> 00:06:56.960 align:middle line:84%
And on the maps, you have
this beautiful picture

00:06:56.960 --> 00:06:58.669 align:middle line:84%
of a big inland
sea, the Aral Sea.

00:06:58.669 --> 00:07:00.460 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the
satellite picture today,

00:07:00.460 --> 00:07:02.040 align:middle line:90%
the Aral Sea is gone.

00:07:02.040 --> 00:07:04.160 align:middle line:84%
The entire sea is
essentially gone.

00:07:04.160 --> 00:07:06.160 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, what
happened to a whole sea that

00:07:06.160 --> 00:07:07.870 align:middle line:84%
was one of the biggest
seas in the world?

00:07:07.870 --> 00:07:10.720 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is people
started to divert the water

00:07:10.720 --> 00:07:13.800 align:middle line:84%
for irrigation of crops in
a desert, and at some point

00:07:13.800 --> 00:07:17.920 align:middle line:84%
not recognizing you can't
change these courses of nature

00:07:17.920 --> 00:07:21.414 align:middle line:84%
without affecting a greater
segment of the environment.

00:07:21.414 --> 00:07:23.330 align:middle line:84%
And so, we really have
to wake up to the fact,

00:07:23.330 --> 00:07:26.500 align:middle line:84%
yes, we are altering the
conditions of the environment,

00:07:26.500 --> 00:07:29.887 align:middle line:84%
changing agriculture,
the amount of pollution

00:07:29.887 --> 00:07:31.720 align:middle line:84%
that we're putting into
the air, all of this

00:07:31.720 --> 00:07:34.380 align:middle line:84%
has a profound effect on
global climate change.

00:07:34.380 --> 00:07:35.800 align:middle line:90%
And so the significance is that.

00:07:35.800 --> 00:07:37.800 align:middle line:84%
Now we're looking around
saying oh, my god, the weather

00:07:37.800 --> 00:07:39.270 align:middle line:90%
is so erratic and so changeable.

00:07:39.270 --> 00:07:41.300 align:middle line:84%
And it's like we
didn't necessarily

00:07:41.300 --> 00:07:44.310 align:middle line:84%
create global warming,
but we are surely

00:07:44.310 --> 00:07:46.070 align:middle line:90%
exacerbating the situation.

00:07:46.070 --> 00:07:47.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, absolutely.

00:07:47.500 --> 00:07:51.080 align:middle line:84%
So how can we take this
global conversation

00:07:51.080 --> 00:07:53.790 align:middle line:84%
and bring it to
a personal level?

00:07:53.790 --> 00:07:57.530 align:middle line:84%
How can we take our
thoughts and direct them

00:07:57.530 --> 00:08:00.270 align:middle line:84%
towards something that
goes towards growth

00:08:00.270 --> 00:08:02.410 align:middle line:90%
and goes towards solution?

00:08:02.410 --> 00:08:04.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: First to
recognize that we

00:08:04.030 --> 00:08:05.820 align:middle line:84%
are active participants
in the process,

00:08:05.820 --> 00:08:07.990 align:middle line:84%
because we sort of take
ourselves out of the picture

00:08:07.990 --> 00:08:10.250 align:middle line:84%
and say, oh, the Earth is
going through this stuff.

00:08:10.250 --> 00:08:12.030 align:middle line:84%
No, the Earth isn't
going through it.

00:08:12.030 --> 00:08:14.580 align:middle line:90%
We are creating this upheaval.

00:08:14.580 --> 00:08:17.320 align:middle line:84%
So it's very interesting
because our beliefs

00:08:17.320 --> 00:08:19.800 align:middle line:84%
shape our cultures
and our civilization.

00:08:19.800 --> 00:08:21.330 align:middle line:84%
And this is why
it's so interesting

00:08:21.330 --> 00:08:25.410 align:middle line:84%
right now, for example, when
we understand the fact is this.

00:08:25.410 --> 00:08:29.860 align:middle line:84%
That civilization as we
know it is coming to an end,

00:08:29.860 --> 00:08:31.620 align:middle line:84%
as we know it is
coming to an end.

00:08:31.620 --> 00:08:33.487 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't mean
the end of humans,

00:08:33.487 --> 00:08:35.820 align:middle line:84%
but it means the end of the
way of life that we're doing

00:08:35.820 --> 00:08:37.748 align:middle line:84%
and a new civilization
is coming forward.

00:08:37.748 --> 00:08:39.289 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this
has happened before.

00:08:39.289 --> 00:08:41.299 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: This-- in
Western civilization, this

00:08:41.299 --> 00:08:43.309 align:middle line:84%
is really the story of
Western civilization.

00:08:43.309 --> 00:08:45.037 align:middle line:84%
We go back over the
past and we say,

00:08:45.037 --> 00:08:46.495 align:middle line:84%
well, there have
been civilizations

00:08:46.495 --> 00:08:47.990 align:middle line:90%
that have come and gone.

00:08:47.990 --> 00:08:50.760 align:middle line:84%
So, for example, we talk
about the Roman civilization.

00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:51.260 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yes.

00:08:51.260 --> 00:08:53.820 align:middle line:84%
There was a Roman
civilization and it's gone.

00:08:53.820 --> 00:08:55.260 align:middle line:90%
And so, what happened here?

00:08:55.260 --> 00:08:57.300 align:middle line:84%
Well, if we just quickly
look at the history

00:08:57.300 --> 00:08:59.559 align:middle line:84%
of Western civilization,
what we find

00:08:59.559 --> 00:09:01.350 align:middle line:84%
is that there were
different civilizations,

00:09:01.350 --> 00:09:03.590 align:middle line:84%
that we started with
a civilization call

00:09:03.590 --> 00:09:05.860 align:middle line:84%
Animism, which is sort of
like the Native Americans,

00:09:05.860 --> 00:09:07.580 align:middle line:84%
the indigenous
people that learned

00:09:07.580 --> 00:09:09.080 align:middle line:84%
to live in harmony
with the world.

00:09:09.080 --> 00:09:11.890 align:middle line:84%
In fact, this is where we really
ultimately have to go back.

00:09:11.890 --> 00:09:14.410 align:middle line:84%
If you just consider what
the Native Americans said,

00:09:14.410 --> 00:09:17.200 align:middle line:84%
for example, that this is
a garden and their role

00:09:17.200 --> 00:09:19.030 align:middle line:90%
was to tend the garden.

00:09:19.030 --> 00:09:23.090 align:middle line:84%
Losing that-- we left
that Animistic period

00:09:23.090 --> 00:09:25.379 align:middle line:84%
and then entered into a
period call Polytheism.

00:09:25.379 --> 00:09:26.920 align:middle line:84%
And that was a
different civilization

00:09:26.920 --> 00:09:30.020 align:middle line:84%
where the Romans, the Greeks,
the Egyptians, many gods,

00:09:30.020 --> 00:09:31.670 align:middle line:90%
et cetera, came up.

00:09:31.670 --> 00:09:34.440 align:middle line:84%
That, like the Roman
civilization, ended.

00:09:34.440 --> 00:09:36.820 align:middle line:84%
And the new civilization
that came out of that

00:09:36.820 --> 00:09:38.520 align:middle line:90%
was called Monotheism.

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:41.860 align:middle line:84%
That's when the Church
of Rome, for example,

00:09:41.860 --> 00:09:45.010 align:middle line:84%
gave the organization
and culture to the people

00:09:45.010 --> 00:09:46.180 align:middle line:90%
on the planet.

00:09:46.180 --> 00:09:49.280 align:middle line:84%
And interestingly enough,
even that civilization

00:09:49.280 --> 00:09:53.820 align:middle line:84%
came to an end about 1870
after Charles Darwin introduced

00:09:53.820 --> 00:09:57.160 align:middle line:84%
the notion of a biological
source of evolution

00:09:57.160 --> 00:10:00.600 align:middle line:84%
rather than the concept
of Genesis, for example.

00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:02.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, in that
place of Monotheism,

00:10:02.750 --> 00:10:04.990 align:middle line:84%
where we had the
particular culture that

00:10:04.990 --> 00:10:09.350 align:middle line:84%
was wrapped around various
religious beliefs and so forth,

00:10:09.350 --> 00:10:13.973 align:middle line:84%
was that designed originally
to grow a society?

00:10:13.973 --> 00:10:16.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, It's
very interesting.

00:10:16.260 --> 00:10:18.344 align:middle line:84%
Many things start out
with a very positive

00:10:18.344 --> 00:10:20.260 align:middle line:84%
this is what we're going
to do for the people.

00:10:20.260 --> 00:10:22.884 align:middle line:84%
It's actually a very interesting
insight if you think about it.

00:10:22.884 --> 00:10:25.350 align:middle line:84%
Many organizations start
out helping people.

00:10:25.350 --> 00:10:28.670 align:middle line:84%
Health care, OK,
education, government.

00:10:28.670 --> 00:10:30.450 align:middle line:84%
And at some point,
their original work

00:10:30.450 --> 00:10:33.020 align:middle line:84%
was indeed really
helping and facilitating

00:10:33.020 --> 00:10:34.760 align:middle line:90%
the growth of a population.

00:10:34.760 --> 00:10:37.506 align:middle line:84%
But if you look back at it,
this is an interesting point,

00:10:37.506 --> 00:10:39.130 align:middle line:84%
is that when they
reach a certain size,

00:10:39.130 --> 00:10:41.560 align:middle line:84%
they become an
institution themselves.

00:10:41.560 --> 00:10:44.387 align:middle line:84%
So all of a sudden,
it's like academia first

00:10:44.387 --> 00:10:46.220 align:middle line:84%
was just some teachers
teaching, but then it

00:10:46.220 --> 00:10:47.207 align:middle line:90%
became a university.

00:10:47.207 --> 00:10:47.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:10:47.790 --> 00:10:48.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: OK.

00:10:48.380 --> 00:10:50.600 align:middle line:84%
And the significance,
once the institution

00:10:50.600 --> 00:10:54.660 align:middle line:84%
became so prominent, then the
efforts of the organization

00:10:54.660 --> 00:10:57.310 align:middle line:84%
actually then are not so
much on helping the people,

00:10:57.310 --> 00:10:59.700 align:middle line:84%
but on sustaining
the organization,

00:10:59.700 --> 00:11:03.047 align:middle line:84%
so that we lose the
benefit for the people

00:11:03.047 --> 00:11:04.755 align:middle line:84%
but we build these
massive organizations.

00:11:04.755 --> 00:11:05.588 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's true.

00:11:05.588 --> 00:11:07.147 align:middle line:84%
It happens with
the justice system,

00:11:07.147 --> 00:11:08.230 align:middle line:90%
it happens with all of it.

00:11:08.230 --> 00:11:08.555 align:middle line:90%
It starts--

00:11:08.555 --> 00:11:08.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Health care.

00:11:08.880 --> 00:11:10.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: -to take on its own.

00:11:10.010 --> 00:11:10.510 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:10.510 --> 00:11:12.530 align:middle line:90%
Its own entity essentially.

00:11:12.530 --> 00:11:14.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: So basically,
they start out pretty good

00:11:14.660 --> 00:11:15.624 align:middle line:90%
and then they go awry.

00:11:15.624 --> 00:11:16.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why is that, though?

00:11:16.790 --> 00:11:18.110 align:middle line:90%
Why does that happen?

00:11:18.110 --> 00:11:20.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, I just
think there's some effort

00:11:20.510 --> 00:11:23.549 align:middle line:84%
to think well, maybe, if we put
more control, that we control

00:11:23.549 --> 00:11:24.090 align:middle line:90%
these things.

00:11:24.090 --> 00:11:26.430 align:middle line:84%
And that's a concept
of if I can control it,

00:11:26.430 --> 00:11:28.490 align:middle line:90%
then we can guide its direction.

00:11:28.490 --> 00:11:31.040 align:middle line:84%
Except, it's OK to
have an idea of control

00:11:31.040 --> 00:11:32.740 align:middle line:90%
if you have knowledge.

00:11:32.740 --> 00:11:34.930 align:middle line:84%
If you don't have knowledge,
then all of a sudden

00:11:34.930 --> 00:11:37.480 align:middle line:84%
your control may
go way off the edge

00:11:37.480 --> 00:11:39.730 align:middle line:84%
and actually you're not
helping people anymore,

00:11:39.730 --> 00:11:44.900 align:middle line:84%
but the net result is really
the damage that is accruing.

00:11:44.900 --> 00:11:47.970 align:middle line:84%
And so as you can see
for this situation,

00:11:47.970 --> 00:11:50.870 align:middle line:84%
we are in a civilization
that is coming to an end.

00:11:50.870 --> 00:11:52.414 align:middle line:84%
And we started off
with a concept--

00:11:52.414 --> 00:11:53.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: As we knew it.

00:11:53.330 --> 00:11:54.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: As we know it.

00:11:54.300 --> 00:11:54.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:11:54.720 --> 00:11:56.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And it's coming to an
end for a very simple reason.

00:11:56.550 --> 00:11:58.758 align:middle line:84%
We look around the world
and we see all these crises.

00:11:58.758 --> 00:12:02.280 align:middle line:84%
Oh, we have a peak fuel crisis,
we have an economic crisis,

00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:06.250 align:middle line:84%
we have political crises,
we have health care crisis.

00:12:06.250 --> 00:12:08.110 align:middle line:84%
We're even facing
religious crises.

00:12:08.110 --> 00:12:09.110 align:middle line:90%
And you say, well, wait.

00:12:09.110 --> 00:12:11.284 align:middle line:84%
Oh, let's talk about this
crisis or this crisis.

00:12:11.284 --> 00:12:11.950 align:middle line:90%
And I go no, no.

00:12:11.950 --> 00:12:13.780 align:middle line:90%
You're missing the point.

00:12:13.780 --> 00:12:16.230 align:middle line:84%
Talking about each crisis
is like looking at this tree

00:12:16.230 --> 00:12:18.300 align:middle line:84%
and here's another tree
and here's another tree.

00:12:18.300 --> 00:12:20.640 align:middle line:84%
The whole point is
pull back and recognize

00:12:20.640 --> 00:12:22.790 align:middle line:84%
all the trees are
making a forest.

00:12:22.790 --> 00:12:25.660 align:middle line:84%
The crises, we see them
as individual events,

00:12:25.660 --> 00:12:29.160 align:middle line:84%
are collectively saying
this is not sustainable

00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:32.120 align:middle line:84%
and that we're seeing
the feedback of we're

00:12:32.120 --> 00:12:36.070 align:middle line:84%
going in the wrong direction and
it's coming back in our face,

00:12:36.070 --> 00:12:39.740 align:middle line:84%
threatening our survival on this
particular planet right now.

00:12:39.740 --> 00:12:42.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you had said now
we went from the Monotheism

00:12:42.400 --> 00:12:44.810 align:middle line:90%
into the survivalistic--

00:12:44.810 --> 00:12:47.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Scientific
from Monotheism.

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:49.610 align:middle line:84%
The current version
of civilization

00:12:49.610 --> 00:12:52.200 align:middle line:84%
is officially
Scientific Materialism.

00:12:52.200 --> 00:12:53.750 align:middle line:84%
So you know what's
very interesting

00:12:53.750 --> 00:12:55.710 align:middle line:84%
to talk about is
that civilizations

00:12:55.710 --> 00:12:57.190 align:middle line:90%
are like living things, OK?

00:12:57.190 --> 00:12:58.490 align:middle line:90%
They have a life cycle.

00:12:58.490 --> 00:13:03.420 align:middle line:84%
Civilizations are created and
then they mature, and then

00:13:03.420 --> 00:13:05.777 align:middle line:84%
at some point they start
to go into a decline.

00:13:05.777 --> 00:13:07.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's very interesting
because in the beginning

00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:10.276 align:middle line:84%
of a civilization, just like
in the beginning of a child's

00:13:10.276 --> 00:13:13.320 align:middle line:84%
life, it's a period filled
with a lot of development.

00:13:13.320 --> 00:13:17.000 align:middle line:84%
It's a period filled with let's
try this and let's try this.

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:20.530 align:middle line:84%
And as a civilization matures,
or as an individual matures,

00:13:20.530 --> 00:13:22.890 align:middle line:84%
then you get like
very rigid beliefs.

00:13:22.890 --> 00:13:25.370 align:middle line:84%
This is the belief,
this is the way it is.

00:13:25.370 --> 00:13:28.060 align:middle line:84%
And then when those
rigid beliefs come in,

00:13:28.060 --> 00:13:30.560 align:middle line:84%
this is the mature
state, so-called, OK?

00:13:30.560 --> 00:13:32.550 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's a
problem with rigidity.

00:13:32.550 --> 00:13:35.070 align:middle line:84%
If you live in a universe
were nothing stays the same,

00:13:35.070 --> 00:13:38.360 align:middle line:84%
it's always dynamically
moving, how can a civilization

00:13:38.360 --> 00:13:39.840 align:middle line:84%
hold on to a belief
and say this is

00:13:39.840 --> 00:13:41.510 align:middle line:90%
the only belief that we have?

00:13:41.510 --> 00:13:43.400 align:middle line:84%
And so, when we
hold these beliefs

00:13:43.400 --> 00:13:45.530 align:middle line:84%
and we hold that
rigid nature of it,

00:13:45.530 --> 00:13:47.690 align:middle line:90%
inevitably leads to challenges.

00:13:47.690 --> 00:13:50.820 align:middle line:84%
So that we go from a rigid
state of this is the way it is

00:13:50.820 --> 00:13:53.410 align:middle line:84%
and we start living that
way like we are now,

00:13:53.410 --> 00:13:55.000 align:middle line:84%
and the result is
but if we're not

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.340 align:middle line:84%
living in harmony with the
planet, then the challenges

00:13:57.340 --> 00:13:59.390 align:middle line:84%
that we're facing are
the crises that we see.

00:13:59.390 --> 00:14:01.200 align:middle line:84%
And what are the
crises referring to?

00:14:01.200 --> 00:14:02.770 align:middle line:84%
They're referring
to the fact the way

00:14:02.770 --> 00:14:06.160 align:middle line:84%
you are living on the planet is
not in harmony with the planet.

00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:08.440 align:middle line:84%
And this is then
the period where

00:14:08.440 --> 00:14:10.610 align:middle line:90%
civilization goes into decline.

00:14:10.610 --> 00:14:13.590 align:middle line:84%
So what you're looking
at now is a world that

00:14:13.590 --> 00:14:16.660 align:middle line:84%
seems to be falling apart,
which it is actually,

00:14:16.660 --> 00:14:20.070 align:middle line:84%
but what's most interesting is
just because a civilization is

00:14:20.070 --> 00:14:22.000 align:middle line:84%
ending, doesn't mean
humans are gone.

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:24.760 align:middle line:84%
There's a new civilization in
the process of being built.

00:14:24.760 --> 00:14:27.630 align:middle line:84%
There's always one
civilization follows another.

00:14:27.630 --> 00:14:28.839 align:middle line:90%
So right now--

00:14:28.839 --> 00:14:29.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's interesting.

00:14:29.880 --> 00:14:32.430 align:middle line:84%
I was speaking with somebody
on the way here today

00:14:32.430 --> 00:14:35.620 align:middle line:84%
and he was saying that
change has happened

00:14:35.620 --> 00:14:37.260 align:middle line:84%
so much in his own
life, and his--

00:14:37.260 --> 00:14:39.260 align:middle line:84%
he gave himself an
analogy as a ship.

00:14:39.260 --> 00:14:41.220 align:middle line:84%
He said, I was a
ship in the ocean

00:14:41.220 --> 00:14:43.600 align:middle line:84%
and I was going steady for
so many years and so many

00:14:43.600 --> 00:14:46.350 align:middle line:84%
years, and all of a sudden,
it wasn't working anymore

00:14:46.350 --> 00:14:46.980 align:middle line:90%
to go steady.

00:14:46.980 --> 00:14:50.800 align:middle line:84%
Things kept changing around me
and corporations were folding

00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:52.810 align:middle line:84%
and environments were
shifting and changing.

00:14:52.810 --> 00:14:55.470 align:middle line:84%
You basically described
the cycle of life.

00:14:55.470 --> 00:14:57.960 align:middle line:84%
So in people thinking
that you can go along

00:14:57.960 --> 00:15:01.820 align:middle line:84%
in a normal course, these days
it is no longer applicable.

00:15:01.820 --> 00:15:03.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: No, because
the belief systems--

00:15:03.570 --> 00:15:05.150 align:middle line:84%
the very fundamental
belief systems

00:15:05.150 --> 00:15:07.275 align:middle line:84%
that shape the culture and
the character of the way

00:15:07.275 --> 00:15:08.250 align:middle line:90%
we live on this planet.

00:15:08.250 --> 00:15:10.850 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we live by belief,
what we think is right,

00:15:10.850 --> 00:15:12.350 align:middle line:90%
so we follow this path.

00:15:12.350 --> 00:15:15.160 align:middle line:84%
If the belief is not right,
then the path we're following

00:15:15.160 --> 00:15:16.746 align:middle line:90%
is going to lead to a dead end.

00:15:16.746 --> 00:15:18.370 align:middle line:84%
And it's very
interesting because we're

00:15:18.370 --> 00:15:20.390 align:middle line:84%
starting to see it
fall apart right now.

00:15:20.390 --> 00:15:22.532 align:middle line:84%
And yet, while people
are getting nervous

00:15:22.532 --> 00:15:23.990 align:middle line:84%
about it falling
apart, I'm the guy

00:15:23.990 --> 00:15:25.710 align:middle line:84%
in the back of the room that's
jumping up and down going,

00:15:25.710 --> 00:15:27.390 align:middle line:90%
yeah, it's falling apart.

00:15:27.390 --> 00:15:29.270 align:middle line:84%
And the reason is
very simply this.

00:15:29.270 --> 00:15:31.680 align:middle line:84%
If we continue the
course we're on,

00:15:31.680 --> 00:15:33.950 align:middle line:84%
science has already
revealed what

00:15:33.950 --> 00:15:36.190 align:middle line:90%
the destination is, extinction.

00:15:36.190 --> 00:15:38.950 align:middle line:84%
So basically it says,
what do we need to do?

00:15:38.950 --> 00:15:39.980 align:middle line:90%
We need to--

00:15:39.980 --> 00:15:40.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Change the course.

00:15:40.390 --> 00:15:41.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: -really reset.

00:15:41.440 --> 00:15:42.540 align:middle line:90%
Change the course.

00:15:42.540 --> 00:15:44.844 align:middle line:84%
Look at life in a different
way and start over again.

00:15:44.844 --> 00:15:46.260 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting
because we're

00:15:46.260 --> 00:15:49.212 align:middle line:84%
facing like the Occupy
Wall Street Movement.

00:15:49.212 --> 00:15:50.170 align:middle line:90%
What does it represent?

00:15:50.170 --> 00:15:52.650 align:middle line:84%
People that are saying,
this isn't working anymore

00:15:52.650 --> 00:15:54.070 align:middle line:84%
and there's got
to be another way.

00:15:54.070 --> 00:15:56.840 align:middle line:84%
Well, this is great
because, as I said,

00:15:56.840 --> 00:16:00.672 align:middle line:84%
keeping the status quo is
death and that opening up

00:16:00.672 --> 00:16:01.380 align:middle line:90%
is something new.

00:16:01.380 --> 00:16:05.770 align:middle line:84%
So a new civilization
begins when

00:16:05.770 --> 00:16:08.630 align:middle line:84%
people start to pull
out of the structure

00:16:08.630 --> 00:16:11.610 align:middle line:84%
and start to consider
another way of life.

00:16:11.610 --> 00:16:15.840 align:middle line:84%
And we call these people
creative minorities

00:16:15.840 --> 00:16:19.380 align:middle line:84%
or cultural creatives,
the Millennial Group.

00:16:19.380 --> 00:16:21.480 align:middle line:84%
And the Millennial
Group, and this

00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:24.370 align:middle line:84%
is profound because this is
nearly half the population

00:16:24.370 --> 00:16:26.490 align:middle line:84%
of the United States or
the planet right now.

00:16:26.490 --> 00:16:27.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The Millennials.

00:16:27.490 --> 00:16:28.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: The Millennials.

00:16:28.220 --> 00:16:29.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: 20-somethings.

00:16:29.010 --> 00:16:30.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well,
actually under 40.

00:16:30.260 --> 00:16:31.134 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Under 40, OK.

00:16:31.134 --> 00:16:32.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Under 40.

00:16:32.150 --> 00:16:34.350 align:middle line:84%
And this represents an
interesting group of people

00:16:34.350 --> 00:16:37.940 align:middle line:84%
because these young people
are finding it very difficult

00:16:37.940 --> 00:16:39.390 align:middle line:90%
to get into the structure.

00:16:39.390 --> 00:16:40.530 align:middle line:90%
They go to school.

00:16:40.530 --> 00:16:42.910 align:middle line:90%
They accumulate debt like crazy.

00:16:42.910 --> 00:16:44.910 align:middle line:84%
They get out of school
and then there's no jobs.

00:16:44.910 --> 00:16:45.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:16:45.430 --> 00:16:46.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And then they
start to feel like, well, I'm

00:16:46.670 --> 00:16:48.100 align:middle line:90%
not part of the system.

00:16:48.100 --> 00:16:50.310 align:middle line:84%
And many of them are like,
what are we going to do?

00:16:50.310 --> 00:16:51.180 align:middle line:90%
We're not part of the system.

00:16:51.180 --> 00:16:52.060 align:middle line:90%
And it's like, oh, wait, wait.

00:16:52.060 --> 00:16:52.934 align:middle line:90%
You don't understand.

00:16:52.934 --> 00:16:55.424 align:middle line:84%
You're playing--
The Millennials play

00:16:55.424 --> 00:16:57.340 align:middle line:84%
one of the most important
roles on this planet

00:16:57.340 --> 00:16:59.280 align:middle line:84%
right now for a
very simple reason.

00:16:59.280 --> 00:17:00.950 align:middle line:84%
Not being part of
the system means

00:17:00.950 --> 00:17:03.570 align:middle line:84%
they're not attached
to the system.

00:17:03.570 --> 00:17:05.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: They're not
part of the old system.

00:17:05.540 --> 00:17:07.706 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: They're not part
of the old system at all.

00:17:07.706 --> 00:17:09.260 align:middle line:84%
And when fewer and
fewer people are

00:17:09.260 --> 00:17:12.650 align:middle line:84%
holding on to the old
system, it becomes easier

00:17:12.650 --> 00:17:16.465 align:middle line:84%
to let the old system break down
and then create a new system.

00:17:16.465 --> 00:17:17.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: New systems beyond that.

00:17:17.810 --> 00:17:18.435 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Yeah.

00:17:18.435 --> 00:17:19.274 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of course.

00:17:19.274 --> 00:17:21.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, people might
be in fear of what's going on

00:17:21.690 --> 00:17:24.950 align:middle line:84%
is really, look, we have to
change our perception of that.

00:17:24.950 --> 00:17:27.400 align:middle line:84%
It is our greatest
hope in the world

00:17:27.400 --> 00:17:30.290 align:middle line:84%
that these Millennials
and the children that

00:17:30.290 --> 00:17:32.856 align:middle line:84%
follow through them will
create a different world

00:17:32.856 --> 00:17:34.480 align:middle line:84%
than the one we're
living in right now.

00:17:34.480 --> 00:17:37.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That will come as a
relief to a lot of people who

00:17:37.120 --> 00:17:38.870 align:middle line:84%
are out of jobs,
that are looking

00:17:38.870 --> 00:17:40.630 align:middle line:84%
for jobs out of college,
can't find them,

00:17:40.630 --> 00:17:42.320 align:middle line:84%
or in a place where
they are trying

00:17:42.320 --> 00:17:46.160 align:middle line:84%
to create their own thing and
validate the fact that possibly

00:17:46.160 --> 00:17:48.739 align:middle line:84%
being an entrepreneur at this
day and age is a good thing.

00:17:48.739 --> 00:17:49.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Oh, absolutely.

00:17:49.780 --> 00:17:52.238 align:middle line:84%
That's what's so exciting is
we're on the edge of something

00:17:52.238 --> 00:17:54.590 align:middle line:84%
so brand new and exciting,
it's not the old path.

00:17:54.590 --> 00:17:57.310 align:middle line:84%
And so this offers a
whole new way of life.

00:17:57.310 --> 00:17:58.860 align:middle line:84%
And what's really
wonderful that I

00:17:58.860 --> 00:18:01.870 align:middle line:84%
see about it is that it really
represents an opportunity

00:18:01.870 --> 00:18:03.730 align:middle line:90%
to create community again.

00:18:03.730 --> 00:18:06.770 align:middle line:84%
We have lost community and
people are acting individually,

00:18:06.770 --> 00:18:10.200 align:middle line:84%
and this is actually stemming
from a Darwinian belief

00:18:10.200 --> 00:18:12.690 align:middle line:84%
that we bought into our
culture that our world is based

00:18:12.690 --> 00:18:15.090 align:middle line:90%
on the survival of the fittest.

00:18:15.090 --> 00:18:16.820 align:middle line:90%
Nature doesn't see that at all.

00:18:16.820 --> 00:18:20.610 align:middle line:84%
Nature really says it's not the
individuals that I care about.

00:18:20.610 --> 00:18:22.900 align:middle line:84%
Nature wants to
know, look, what's

00:18:22.900 --> 00:18:24.120 align:middle line:90%
the human population doing?

00:18:24.120 --> 00:18:26.570 align:middle line:84%
Don't tell me about
Mozart and don't tell me

00:18:26.570 --> 00:18:30.339 align:middle line:84%
about Einstein or Davinci,
those are wonderful individuals.

00:18:30.339 --> 00:18:32.630 align:middle line:84%
But it's not the individuals
nature is concerned about.

00:18:32.630 --> 00:18:34.380 align:middle line:90%
It's the mass of people.

00:18:34.380 --> 00:18:37.090 align:middle line:90%
What are we as a group doing?

00:18:37.090 --> 00:18:39.820 align:middle line:84%
And the fact is, well,
we're destroying the planet.

00:18:39.820 --> 00:18:42.084 align:middle line:84%
And we're doing it under a
cultural belief that says,

00:18:42.084 --> 00:18:43.625 align:middle line:84%
well, there's a
struggle for survival

00:18:43.625 --> 00:18:47.740 align:middle line:84%
and we must go out there and
fight each other for fitness.

00:18:47.740 --> 00:18:50.830 align:middle line:84%
Well, the issue is
evolution really

00:18:50.830 --> 00:18:52.455 align:middle line:84%
isn't based on a
struggle for survival.

00:18:52.455 --> 00:18:54.163 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Struggle for
survival any longer.

00:18:54.163 --> 00:18:54.880 align:middle line:90%
Well, it isn't.

00:18:54.880 --> 00:18:55.380 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:18:55.380 --> 00:18:56.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: It's a
cooperative event.

00:18:56.970 --> 00:18:58.420 align:middle line:90%
And how do you get cooperation?

00:18:58.420 --> 00:19:00.690 align:middle line:84%
People have to come back
together in a community.

00:19:00.690 --> 00:19:02.649 align:middle line:84%
When we were looking at
us individualistically,

00:19:02.649 --> 00:19:05.023 align:middle line:84%
then I say, well, I don't care
I'm part of the community.

00:19:05.023 --> 00:19:07.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to make myself
the fittest, the survival

00:19:07.200 --> 00:19:09.820 align:middle line:84%
of the fittest, so I don't
care about the community.

00:19:09.820 --> 00:19:11.820 align:middle line:90%
The new evolution says, no.

00:19:11.820 --> 00:19:14.780 align:middle line:84%
It's the community that
provides for the evolution, not

00:19:14.780 --> 00:19:15.490 align:middle line:90%
the individual.

00:19:15.490 --> 00:19:18.810 align:middle line:84%
So that's why I get
very enthusiastic to see

00:19:18.810 --> 00:19:20.650 align:middle line:84%
the young people
out in the streets,

00:19:20.650 --> 00:19:22.770 align:middle line:84%
the young people saying
there's a better way,

00:19:22.770 --> 00:19:25.034 align:middle line:90%
rejecting the system, because--

00:19:25.034 --> 00:19:25.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: They're right.

00:19:25.950 --> 00:19:26.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: They're right.

00:19:26.950 --> 00:19:28.412 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
we're now going.

00:19:28.412 --> 00:19:29.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So these
are some old myths

00:19:29.870 --> 00:19:32.439 align:middle line:84%
that you're breaking down,
these are some old ways

00:19:32.439 --> 00:19:33.980 align:middle line:84%
of thinking that
you're breaking down

00:19:33.980 --> 00:19:35.930 align:middle line:84%
in order to bring about
the new ways of thinking.

00:19:35.930 --> 00:19:36.804 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely.

00:19:36.804 --> 00:19:40.080 align:middle line:84%
You see, it's very interesting
because a civilization

00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:41.560 align:middle line:90%
is based on a set of beliefs.

00:19:41.560 --> 00:19:42.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:19:42.060 --> 00:19:42.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: OK.

00:19:42.950 --> 00:19:45.840 align:middle line:84%
And the beliefs are beliefs
related to the answers

00:19:45.840 --> 00:19:48.090 align:middle line:84%
to three fundamental
questions that

00:19:48.090 --> 00:19:50.540 align:middle line:84%
have been around for 10,000
years, the same questions

00:19:50.540 --> 00:19:51.980 align:middle line:90%
10,000 years, OK?

00:19:51.980 --> 00:19:54.670 align:middle line:84%
These questions are called
the Perennial Questions.

00:19:54.670 --> 00:19:57.710 align:middle line:84%
The Perennial Questions
are how did we get here,

00:19:57.710 --> 00:19:59.640 align:middle line:84%
why are we here, and
now that we're here,

00:19:59.640 --> 00:20:01.030 align:middle line:90%
how do we make the best of it.

00:20:01.030 --> 00:20:01.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:20:01.700 --> 00:20:03.866 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, a very
interesting aspect about that

00:20:03.866 --> 00:20:05.640 align:middle line:90%
is simply this.

00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:08.550 align:middle line:84%
Whoever provides the
answers to the questions

00:20:08.550 --> 00:20:12.700 align:middle line:84%
that the public accepts,
two fundamental consequences

00:20:12.700 --> 00:20:14.430 align:middle line:90%
of that answer.

00:20:14.430 --> 00:20:18.100 align:middle line:84%
Number one, the answers
give shape to the culture.

00:20:18.100 --> 00:20:19.900 align:middle line:84%
And so basically
it says, if this

00:20:19.900 --> 00:20:21.880 align:middle line:84%
is what we believe
how life is to work,

00:20:21.880 --> 00:20:24.440 align:middle line:84%
then the culture will build
itself to that belief.

00:20:24.440 --> 00:20:26.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It shapes how the
culture is formed, OK.

00:20:26.820 --> 00:20:30.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: So basically the
answers to the questions shape

00:20:30.280 --> 00:20:30.780 align:middle line:90%
the culture.

00:20:30.780 --> 00:20:32.238 align:middle line:84%
These are the
fundamental questions

00:20:32.238 --> 00:20:34.460 align:middle line:84%
and they are the
fundamental answers

00:20:34.460 --> 00:20:36.320 align:middle line:84%
that shape the world
that we live in.

00:20:36.320 --> 00:20:40.100 align:middle line:84%
And number two, whoever
provides us with those answers

00:20:40.100 --> 00:20:41.790 align:middle line:84%
also becomes what
we call the truth

00:20:41.790 --> 00:20:43.260 align:middle line:90%
provider for that civilization.

00:20:43.260 --> 00:20:45.690 align:middle line:84%
So questions other than
how did we get here

00:20:45.690 --> 00:20:48.070 align:middle line:84%
and why are we here,
all the other questions

00:20:48.070 --> 00:20:50.070 align:middle line:84%
are also directed
to these people.

00:20:50.070 --> 00:20:52.455 align:middle line:84%
So if we go back, let's say
the previous civilization

00:20:52.455 --> 00:20:54.340 align:middle line:90%
is Monotheism, OK?

00:20:54.340 --> 00:20:56.805 align:middle line:84%
And in Monotheism
I say, well, how

00:20:56.805 --> 00:20:59.180 align:middle line:84%
did you answer the questions
and who gave us the answers?

00:20:59.180 --> 00:21:01.050 align:middle line:84%
Well, the answers
came from the church.

00:21:01.050 --> 00:21:01.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:21:01.800 --> 00:21:03.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And the question
was how did we get here,

00:21:03.100 --> 00:21:05.230 align:middle line:84%
and the answer was
divine intervention.

00:21:05.230 --> 00:21:07.400 align:middle line:84%
The Sistine Chapel,
David and God

00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:09.140 align:middle line:84%
with the little
fingers like that.

00:21:09.140 --> 00:21:11.060 align:middle line:84%
And they said, well,
why are we here?

00:21:11.060 --> 00:21:15.300 align:middle line:84%
Well, according to the church,
the spiritual world isn't here.

00:21:15.300 --> 00:21:16.860 align:middle line:84%
The spiritual world
is off planet.

00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:18.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Outside of us, yes.

00:21:18.020 --> 00:21:19.686 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And so what
are we doing here?

00:21:19.686 --> 00:21:22.200 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is we're
testing ourselves.

00:21:22.200 --> 00:21:24.235 align:middle line:84%
We're seeing if we're
worthy enough to-

00:21:24.235 --> 00:21:25.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: To get there.

00:21:25.110 --> 00:21:25.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: -go to
the other place.

00:21:25.990 --> 00:21:28.070 align:middle line:84%
So then it says, then
your life on this planet

00:21:28.070 --> 00:21:30.010 align:middle line:84%
is to live out
plays of morality,

00:21:30.010 --> 00:21:33.890 align:middle line:84%
meaning is your life worthy
enough to go to the next place?

00:21:33.890 --> 00:21:34.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:21:34.430 --> 00:21:35.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And they say, well,
how do you make the best of it?

00:21:35.890 --> 00:21:36.860 align:middle line:90%
How can you do that?

00:21:36.860 --> 00:21:39.240 align:middle line:84%
And according to the
church, is just follow

00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:40.280 align:middle line:90%
the laws of the Bible.

00:21:40.280 --> 00:21:43.670 align:middle line:84%
So then they tell us these
are the rules of the Bible.

00:21:43.670 --> 00:21:46.570 align:middle line:84%
Once we bought those
answers and the civilization

00:21:46.570 --> 00:21:49.840 align:middle line:84%
called Monotheism was created
from a previous civilization,

00:21:49.840 --> 00:21:53.640 align:middle line:84%
Polytheism, the church not
only provided those answers,

00:21:53.640 --> 00:21:55.520 align:middle line:84%
but the church was the
source of our truth.

00:21:55.520 --> 00:21:56.894 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it
provided-- it made

00:21:56.894 --> 00:21:59.140 align:middle line:84%
us believe that our answers
are outside of ourselves.

00:21:59.140 --> 00:22:00.014 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely.

00:22:00.014 --> 00:22:03.310 align:middle line:84%
And it separated us from
our spiritual connection.

00:22:03.310 --> 00:22:05.820 align:middle line:84%
So it sort of said,
look, we're the interface

00:22:05.820 --> 00:22:06.847 align:middle line:90%
between you and God.

00:22:06.847 --> 00:22:08.430 align:middle line:84%
And if you really
want to go with God,

00:22:08.430 --> 00:22:10.055 align:middle line:84%
then you have to
really walk through us

00:22:10.055 --> 00:22:12.360 align:middle line:84%
and we'll guide you
there and help you there,

00:22:12.360 --> 00:22:15.170 align:middle line:84%
and maybe you could
pay for your way there.

00:22:15.170 --> 00:22:16.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But it'll cost you.

00:22:16.590 --> 00:22:17.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Exactly.

00:22:17.830 --> 00:22:19.500 align:middle line:84%
It's sort of an
interesting club,

00:22:19.500 --> 00:22:21.610 align:middle line:84%
because they also
made a club out of it.

00:22:21.610 --> 00:22:23.950 align:middle line:84%
You're either part of our
organization or your dead.

00:22:23.950 --> 00:22:25.084 align:middle line:90%
And so, it's like, OK.

00:22:25.084 --> 00:22:25.875 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:22:25.875 --> 00:22:26.280 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:22:26.280 --> 00:22:28.279 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And that really
put everybody together

00:22:28.279 --> 00:22:31.170 align:middle line:84%
and we then sought answers
to everything about life

00:22:31.170 --> 00:22:34.870 align:middle line:84%
from the guys wearing the
black frocks, the priests.

00:22:34.870 --> 00:22:38.140 align:middle line:84%
Well, this was the shaping
of that civilization.

00:22:38.140 --> 00:22:41.190 align:middle line:84%
At least there was a morality,
even if it wasn't operating

00:22:41.190 --> 00:22:43.700 align:middle line:84%
that way, there was
a morality behind it.

00:22:43.700 --> 00:22:47.790 align:middle line:84%
But the concepts change when
the answer to the first question

00:22:47.790 --> 00:22:48.290 align:middle line:90%
changes.

00:22:48.290 --> 00:22:50.384 align:middle line:84%
The first question was
how did we get here?

00:22:50.384 --> 00:22:52.550 align:middle line:84%
Well, the Church gave us
the whole story of Genesis,

00:22:52.550 --> 00:22:54.510 align:middle line:84%
the seven days of magic,
and all that kind of stuff.

00:22:54.510 --> 00:22:55.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Adam and Eve, yes.

00:22:55.650 --> 00:22:56.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Yeah.

00:22:56.870 --> 00:23:02.370 align:middle line:84%
In about 1870, about 10 years
after Charles Darwin's "Origin

00:23:02.370 --> 00:23:05.190 align:middle line:84%
of Species" book,
civilization changed

00:23:05.190 --> 00:23:07.970 align:middle line:84%
because they accepted
a different answer.

00:23:07.970 --> 00:23:10.200 align:middle line:84%
And this new
civilization is what

00:23:10.200 --> 00:23:12.490 align:middle line:84%
we call Scientific
Materialism, OK?

00:23:12.490 --> 00:23:16.720 align:middle line:84%
So in Scientific Materialism,
I say, well, science took over.

00:23:16.720 --> 00:23:18.945 align:middle line:84%
What answers to the
questions did they provide?

00:23:18.945 --> 00:23:20.820 align:middle line:84%
So the first question
is how did we get here?

00:23:20.820 --> 00:23:22.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, the Darwinian
idea was oh, we

00:23:22.290 --> 00:23:24.290 align:middle line:84%
got here through random
genetic mutations.

00:23:24.290 --> 00:23:26.850 align:middle line:84%
It was just these
accidental mutations

00:23:26.850 --> 00:23:28.330 align:middle line:90%
that ultimately led to us.

00:23:28.330 --> 00:23:30.050 align:middle line:90%
And we say, oh, OK, cool.

00:23:30.050 --> 00:23:32.490 align:middle line:84%
Which really has great
influence on the second question

00:23:32.490 --> 00:23:34.080 align:middle line:90%
of why are we here?

00:23:34.080 --> 00:23:38.020 align:middle line:84%
This is a trouble spot because
according to a random mutation

00:23:38.020 --> 00:23:39.382 align:middle line:90%
consequence, why are we here?

00:23:39.382 --> 00:23:41.340 align:middle line:84%
And you say, well, I
don't know why we're here,

00:23:41.340 --> 00:23:42.740 align:middle line:90%
it was just an accident.

00:23:42.740 --> 00:23:45.310 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
humans had lost

00:23:45.310 --> 00:23:47.070 align:middle line:84%
a real purpose in
their existence.

00:23:47.070 --> 00:23:48.400 align:middle line:90%
Oh, we're here.

00:23:48.400 --> 00:23:48.900 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:23:48.900 --> 00:23:50.210 align:middle line:90%
Well, genetics.

00:23:50.210 --> 00:23:50.980 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:23:50.980 --> 00:23:52.750 align:middle line:90%
Accident, we don't know why.

00:23:52.750 --> 00:23:56.240 align:middle line:84%
And then the worst part of
the Scientific Materialism

00:23:56.240 --> 00:23:57.880 align:middle line:90%
comes in the third question.

00:23:57.880 --> 00:24:00.620 align:middle line:84%
The third question, well, how
do you make the best of it?

00:24:00.620 --> 00:24:03.560 align:middle line:84%
Well, when the
foundational insight

00:24:03.560 --> 00:24:05.770 align:middle line:84%
to the Theory of
Evolution is that we

00:24:05.770 --> 00:24:08.820 align:middle line:84%
are facing a
struggle for survival

00:24:08.820 --> 00:24:11.850 align:middle line:90%
in our effort to exist.

00:24:11.850 --> 00:24:15.220 align:middle line:84%
And that built in the concept
of the survival of the fittest

00:24:15.220 --> 00:24:18.620 align:middle line:84%
and said, this is
a jungle out here.

00:24:18.620 --> 00:24:20.710 align:middle line:84%
And how do you make
the best of it?

00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:22.690 align:middle line:84%
You live by the
laws of the jungle.

00:24:22.690 --> 00:24:25.770 align:middle line:84%
Now what's really interesting,
well, the previous generation,

00:24:25.770 --> 00:24:29.030 align:middle line:84%
Monotheism, at least had a
moral aspect of your life

00:24:29.030 --> 00:24:32.170 align:middle line:84%
should be something like
morally appropriate.

00:24:32.170 --> 00:24:34.545 align:middle line:84%
When it came to science,
science didn't offer morality.

00:24:34.545 --> 00:24:36.640 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't its job to do that.

00:24:36.640 --> 00:24:38.389 align:middle line:84%
Science's job is to
say how does it work?

00:24:38.389 --> 00:24:39.930 align:middle line:84%
And so science says,
look, it's based

00:24:39.930 --> 00:24:41.221 align:middle line:90%
on the survival of the fittest.

00:24:41.221 --> 00:24:45.350 align:middle line:84%
Well, the question is
that's the end, survival.

00:24:45.350 --> 00:24:47.499 align:middle line:84%
What is the means
to get to that end?

00:24:47.499 --> 00:24:49.082 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's where
science says, look,

00:24:49.082 --> 00:24:50.456 align:middle line:84%
it's not my job
to tell you that.

00:24:50.456 --> 00:24:52.990 align:middle line:84%
If you're the last one
standing, then you win, OK?

00:24:52.990 --> 00:24:55.660 align:middle line:84%
Well, what is the means
to get to the end,

00:24:55.660 --> 00:24:59.600 align:middle line:84%
you know like with Albert
Einstein or Mozart.

00:24:59.600 --> 00:25:02.740 align:middle line:84%
Is that what we're looking for
as a survival of the fittest?

00:25:02.740 --> 00:25:04.470 align:middle line:84%
And I say, well,
that could work,

00:25:04.470 --> 00:25:08.880 align:middle line:84%
but some jerk with an AK-47
could also be the last one.

00:25:08.880 --> 00:25:11.250 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden
you say, oh, my god.

00:25:11.250 --> 00:25:15.114 align:middle line:84%
We can do anything
it takes to succeed.

00:25:15.114 --> 00:25:16.780 align:middle line:84%
And when you look at
the world around us

00:25:16.780 --> 00:25:19.670 align:middle line:84%
you start to see, oh, my God,
people are ripping each other

00:25:19.670 --> 00:25:22.310 align:middle line:84%
off, people are
dominating each other.

00:25:22.310 --> 00:25:25.644 align:middle line:84%
And they do it not like
in a hostile manner,

00:25:25.644 --> 00:25:28.060 align:middle line:84%
they do it because they say
look at what the science said.

00:25:28.060 --> 00:25:29.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I need to survive.

00:25:29.270 --> 00:25:31.125 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And I can do
anything to survive.

00:25:31.125 --> 00:25:33.500 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting because
when we bought the questions

00:25:33.500 --> 00:25:36.870 align:middle line:84%
from science, we also made
science a truth provider.

00:25:36.870 --> 00:25:38.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And science went
up against Monotheism

00:25:38.990 --> 00:25:39.853 align:middle line:90%
in a competitive--

00:25:39.853 --> 00:25:40.196 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely.

00:25:40.196 --> 00:25:40.737 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: -way.

00:25:40.737 --> 00:25:43.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And so no
longer do the people

00:25:43.140 --> 00:25:46.630 align:middle line:84%
in today's civilization go
to the black-coated priests

00:25:46.630 --> 00:25:49.889 align:middle line:84%
for their truths, we go to the
white-coated priests called

00:25:49.889 --> 00:25:50.555 align:middle line:90%
the scientists--

00:25:50.555 --> 00:25:51.346 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting

00:25:51.346 --> 00:25:53.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: -who offer
us their answers.

00:25:53.000 --> 00:25:57.460 align:middle line:84%
So now this is OK-- if
the beliefs of science

00:25:57.460 --> 00:26:01.900 align:middle line:84%
are accurate, then following
their suggestions is

00:26:01.900 --> 00:26:03.210 align:middle line:90%
going to be great.

00:26:03.210 --> 00:26:06.950 align:middle line:84%
But if the beliefs are not
accurate, at that point

00:26:06.950 --> 00:26:10.500 align:middle line:84%
then it says those beliefs
could lead us to a termination.

00:26:10.500 --> 00:26:11.244 align:middle line:90%
Yes, exactly.

00:26:11.244 --> 00:26:12.910 align:middle line:84%
The extinction we've
been talking about.

00:26:12.910 --> 00:26:14.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So the
Darwinian philosophies

00:26:14.860 --> 00:26:17.430 align:middle line:84%
that you're talking about,
the survival of the fittest,

00:26:17.430 --> 00:26:20.129 align:middle line:84%
are the old science in
what your opinion is.

00:26:20.129 --> 00:26:21.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Oh, absolutely.

00:26:21.170 --> 00:26:23.060 align:middle line:84%
And it's destructive
science because that's

00:26:23.060 --> 00:26:26.190 align:middle line:84%
what we're living by, that's our
cultural way of life right now.

00:26:26.190 --> 00:26:28.770 align:middle line:84%
It says, look, if I
happen to beat you

00:26:28.770 --> 00:26:30.780 align:middle line:84%
and you're in the
ground, well, that's OK

00:26:30.780 --> 00:26:33.219 align:middle line:84%
because that's
the law of nature.

00:26:33.219 --> 00:26:35.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to beat you in
survival of the fittest.

00:26:35.260 --> 00:26:37.290 align:middle line:84%
And so you might
say, well, then OK,

00:26:37.290 --> 00:26:41.210 align:middle line:84%
if we're facing our extinction
because of this issue

00:26:41.210 --> 00:26:43.110 align:middle line:84%
about our beliefs
not being correct,

00:26:43.110 --> 00:26:44.390 align:middle line:90%
what should we do about it?

00:26:44.390 --> 00:26:47.740 align:middle line:84%
And I love it because
Albert Einstein,

00:26:47.740 --> 00:26:49.550 align:middle line:84%
he's one of my great
heroes of course.

00:26:49.550 --> 00:26:52.030 align:middle line:84%
Albert Einstein came
up with a very simple

00:26:52.030 --> 00:26:53.510 align:middle line:90%
often-repeated phrase.

00:26:53.510 --> 00:26:56.510 align:middle line:84%
People have heard it a lot,
but to me it's most important

00:26:56.510 --> 00:27:00.580 align:middle line:84%
at this moment and that is you
cannot solve the problems with

00:27:00.580 --> 00:27:03.750 align:middle line:84%
the same thinking that
created the problems.

00:27:03.750 --> 00:27:05.300 align:middle line:90%
The issue is this.

00:27:05.300 --> 00:27:09.290 align:middle line:84%
The institutions that we live
by-- science, government,

00:27:09.290 --> 00:27:11.720 align:middle line:84%
academia, et cetera--
have provided us

00:27:11.720 --> 00:27:15.180 align:middle line:84%
with belief systems, and we have
been following these beliefs.

00:27:15.180 --> 00:27:18.382 align:middle line:84%
And in following these beliefs,
now we face our own extinction.

00:27:18.382 --> 00:27:19.090 align:middle line:90%
What's the point?

00:27:19.090 --> 00:27:21.880 align:middle line:84%
The point is we have
to change the path.

00:27:21.880 --> 00:27:24.700 align:middle line:84%
And that's why so-- you know,
so people should recognize when

00:27:24.700 --> 00:27:28.900 align:middle line:84%
you see the institutions having
trouble, this is not bad.

00:27:28.900 --> 00:27:31.450 align:middle line:84%
It's because it's
the beliefs provided

00:27:31.450 --> 00:27:32.864 align:middle line:90%
by those institutions--

00:27:32.864 --> 00:27:35.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it's those old
beliefs, those old systems that

00:27:35.280 --> 00:27:37.990 align:middle line:84%
are breaking down, which is
what we're experience, right?

00:27:37.990 --> 00:27:39.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Right, so when
you see it falling down,

00:27:39.620 --> 00:27:41.400 align:middle line:84%
you could look at it two
ways and go oh, my god, it's

00:27:41.400 --> 00:27:42.316 align:middle line:90%
the end of the system.

00:27:42.316 --> 00:27:43.560 align:middle line:90%
And I go yeah, great.

00:27:43.560 --> 00:27:46.600 align:middle line:84%
Because if it doesn't end,
extinction is the result.

00:27:46.600 --> 00:27:49.530 align:middle line:84%
So stand back and look at
it and say, yes, it's time

00:27:49.530 --> 00:27:51.950 align:middle line:84%
to change the beliefs
to live in a greater

00:27:51.950 --> 00:27:55.030 align:middle line:84%
harmony with the world than
with each other because we

00:27:55.030 --> 00:27:56.520 align:middle line:84%
are, indeed, facing
this evolution.

00:27:56.520 --> 00:27:59.940 align:middle line:84%
It is very exciting to be
alive now for this reason.

00:27:59.940 --> 00:28:04.460 align:middle line:84%
We are actually witnessing the
evolution of human civilization

00:28:04.460 --> 00:28:06.480 align:middle line:90%
to the next higher level.

00:28:06.480 --> 00:28:08.415 align:middle line:84%
Right now, we look
at human civilization

00:28:08.415 --> 00:28:10.849 align:middle line:84%
as individuals
competing and trying

00:28:10.849 --> 00:28:11.890 align:middle line:90%
to survive in this world.

00:28:11.890 --> 00:28:12.473 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:28:12.473 --> 00:28:13.100 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:28:13.100 --> 00:28:14.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: The
evolution we're facing

00:28:14.600 --> 00:28:17.474 align:middle line:84%
is not we're going to evolve and
change who we are biologically.

00:28:17.474 --> 00:28:18.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're not
going to expire.

00:28:18.890 --> 00:28:19.370 align:middle line:90%
We're--

00:28:19.370 --> 00:28:19.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: No.

00:28:19.730 --> 00:28:20.229 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:28:20.229 --> 00:28:21.776 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What we
knew is expiring.

00:28:21.776 --> 00:28:22.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Well, yeah.

00:28:22.650 --> 00:28:24.560 align:middle line:84%
The way we organize
is going to change.

00:28:24.560 --> 00:28:26.430 align:middle line:90%
What we're realizing is this.

00:28:26.430 --> 00:28:29.310 align:middle line:84%
We're going to learn, and
we're learning it right now,

00:28:29.310 --> 00:28:31.260 align:middle line:84%
humans are not
separate entities.

00:28:31.260 --> 00:28:34.750 align:middle line:84%
Humans collectively
are a super organism.

00:28:34.750 --> 00:28:39.210 align:middle line:84%
Each human is like a cell in
the body of a super organism

00:28:39.210 --> 00:28:40.730 align:middle line:90%
called humanity.

00:28:40.730 --> 00:28:43.350 align:middle line:84%
And that becomes important
because it says every human,

00:28:43.350 --> 00:28:45.100 align:middle line:84%
I don't care where
they are on the planet,

00:28:45.100 --> 00:28:47.050 align:middle line:90%
are part of the same humanity.

00:28:47.050 --> 00:28:49.019 align:middle line:84%
And when you have
a living system,

00:28:49.019 --> 00:28:51.310 align:middle line:84%
let's say a human body, in
which the cells are fighting

00:28:51.310 --> 00:28:53.490 align:middle line:84%
each other, that's
a disease called

00:28:53.490 --> 00:28:56.140 align:middle line:84%
autoimmune disease,
which a lot of people

00:28:56.140 --> 00:28:58.664 align:middle line:84%
are affected by because what's
going on in the outer world

00:28:58.664 --> 00:29:00.455 align:middle line:84%
is also being reflected
in the inner world.

00:29:00.455 --> 00:29:00.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:29:00.730 --> 00:29:03.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: So the increase
in autoimmune disease,

00:29:03.130 --> 00:29:06.980 align:middle line:84%
which in Latin simply
means self-destruction,

00:29:06.980 --> 00:29:09.190 align:middle line:84%
we are facing that on
the planet now where

00:29:09.190 --> 00:29:12.180 align:middle line:84%
people have been fighting each
other and killing each other

00:29:12.180 --> 00:29:13.200 align:middle line:90%
and all that.

00:29:13.200 --> 00:29:15.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's reflective of
what's going on in our world--

00:29:15.960 --> 00:29:16.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely.

00:29:16.250 --> 00:29:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: -what's going
on in our bodies.

00:29:16.860 --> 00:29:18.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Our biology
is a complement

00:29:18.700 --> 00:29:20.460 align:middle line:84%
to the world in
which we live, so

00:29:20.460 --> 00:29:22.270 align:middle line:84%
that we're beginning
to see a change.

00:29:22.270 --> 00:29:25.300 align:middle line:84%
And especially the Millennials
are very critical aspects

00:29:25.300 --> 00:29:27.720 align:middle line:84%
of this new evolution
for a simple reason.

00:29:27.720 --> 00:29:30.610 align:middle line:84%
The nervous system
of this new structure

00:29:30.610 --> 00:29:33.720 align:middle line:84%
called humanity is
called the internet.

00:29:33.720 --> 00:29:39.180 align:middle line:84%
It's what connects 7 billion
cells into one system.

00:29:39.180 --> 00:29:40.950 align:middle line:84%
And what I so
appreciate about it

00:29:40.950 --> 00:29:43.430 align:middle line:84%
is when I travel
around the world

00:29:43.430 --> 00:29:45.380 align:middle line:84%
and I see other people
and young people

00:29:45.380 --> 00:29:48.511 align:middle line:84%
in all these other worlds, what
I start to realize-- it's like

00:29:48.511 --> 00:29:50.135 align:middle line:84%
if I'm in Russia--
when I was in Russia

00:29:50.135 --> 00:29:51.640 align:middle line:84%
and I look at the
young people and I go,

00:29:51.640 --> 00:29:53.230 align:middle line:84%
well, it's hard to
tell the difference

00:29:53.230 --> 00:29:54.550 align:middle line:84%
between these young
people in Russia

00:29:54.550 --> 00:29:56.560 align:middle line:84%
and the young people in
Santa Cruz, California.

00:29:56.560 --> 00:29:58.560 align:middle line:90%
And I start to recognize, yes.

00:29:58.560 --> 00:30:01.600 align:middle line:84%
They're beginning to recognize,
the younger people, they're

00:30:01.600 --> 00:30:05.330 align:middle line:84%
not part of this warring,
violent structure that

00:30:05.330 --> 00:30:08.500 align:middle line:84%
has preceded in our
history right now.

00:30:08.500 --> 00:30:10.540 align:middle line:84%
They, themselves, are
beginning to recognize--

00:30:10.540 --> 00:30:12.970 align:middle line:84%
they're the ones that are
recognizing that humans

00:30:12.970 --> 00:30:14.760 align:middle line:90%
are the same all over the place.

00:30:14.760 --> 00:30:19.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the whole Arab Spring
was internet generated.

00:30:19.310 --> 00:30:21.902 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's all-- it's
creating its entire own culture,

00:30:21.902 --> 00:30:22.735 align:middle line:90%
its own environment.

00:30:22.735 --> 00:30:23.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Exactly.

00:30:23.000 --> 00:30:24.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's so interesting.

00:30:24.470 --> 00:30:25.469 align:middle line:90%
That's very interesting.

00:30:25.469 --> 00:30:28.780 align:middle line:84%
So now these old myths
that are being broken down,

00:30:28.780 --> 00:30:30.960 align:middle line:90%
what are the new structures?

00:30:30.960 --> 00:30:31.760 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:30:31.760 --> 00:30:33.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, I
refer to what are

00:30:33.590 --> 00:30:37.040 align:middle line:84%
called the four myths
of the apocalypse.

00:30:37.040 --> 00:30:40.890 align:middle line:84%
And what I mean by this is these
are for beliefs that we bought

00:30:40.890 --> 00:30:44.060 align:middle line:84%
from science that if we continue
following these beliefs,

00:30:44.060 --> 00:30:47.000 align:middle line:84%
then we will inevitably see
the apocalypse that science is

00:30:47.000 --> 00:30:49.240 align:middle line:90%
suggesting is in our future, OK?

00:30:49.240 --> 00:30:49.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:30:49.740 --> 00:30:53.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And what's interesting
is these four beliefs science

00:30:53.020 --> 00:30:56.441 align:middle line:84%
provided for us during the
last couple hundred years,

00:30:56.441 --> 00:30:58.690 align:middle line:84%
and we have shaped our culture
based on these beliefs.

00:30:58.690 --> 00:31:00.560 align:middle line:84%
And now it turns out
that these beliefs

00:31:00.560 --> 00:31:02.420 align:middle line:90%
are flawed or outright wrong.

00:31:02.420 --> 00:31:04.210 align:middle line:84%
And the significance
is by following them,

00:31:04.210 --> 00:31:06.360 align:middle line:84%
that's why we're
facing our destruction.

00:31:06.360 --> 00:31:07.740 align:middle line:90%
So let's just list the four.

00:31:07.740 --> 00:31:08.165 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What are they?

00:31:08.165 --> 00:31:08.665 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, OK.

00:31:08.665 --> 00:31:11.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: The first belief
is that biology, or our life

00:31:11.830 --> 00:31:14.600 align:middle line:84%
sciences, are run by
Newtonian physics.

00:31:14.600 --> 00:31:16.320 align:middle line:84%
And you go, so what
does that mean?

00:31:16.320 --> 00:31:19.190 align:middle line:84%
I say, well, the significance
of Newtonian physics

00:31:19.190 --> 00:31:21.560 align:middle line:84%
is that it's a physics that
emphasizes the material

00:31:21.560 --> 00:31:24.020 align:middle line:84%
universe and ignores
the invisible world.

00:31:24.020 --> 00:31:26.890 align:middle line:84%
It says everything that's
physical is real, count on it,

00:31:26.890 --> 00:31:28.440 align:middle line:90%
and that's what it's all about.

00:31:28.440 --> 00:31:30.290 align:middle line:84%
But the invisible
stuff, not too relevant.

00:31:30.290 --> 00:31:30.810 align:middle line:90%
Who cares?

00:31:30.810 --> 00:31:32.143 align:middle line:90%
And the invisible stuff is what?

00:31:32.143 --> 00:31:35.790 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness, spirit,
emotions, all these things.

00:31:35.790 --> 00:31:36.507 align:middle line:90%
It's like no, no.

00:31:36.507 --> 00:31:38.590 align:middle line:84%
Just look at the physical
body, look at the cells,

00:31:38.590 --> 00:31:39.506 align:middle line:90%
look at the chemistry.

00:31:39.506 --> 00:31:41.720 align:middle line:84%
So this is the way science
looks at human health,

00:31:41.720 --> 00:31:43.790 align:middle line:84%
just like the
physical nature of it.

00:31:43.790 --> 00:31:46.190 align:middle line:90%
And we say, what about the mind?

00:31:46.190 --> 00:31:48.290 align:middle line:84%
And they go, mind's
not relevant.

00:31:48.290 --> 00:31:49.910 align:middle line:84%
It's your chemistry
and your genes.

00:31:49.910 --> 00:31:51.326 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: When you
go to the doctor,

00:31:51.326 --> 00:31:54.120 align:middle line:84%
they give you the physical
reading and diagnosis and then

00:31:54.120 --> 00:31:55.954 align:middle line:84%
a medication and that's
what you get, right?

00:31:55.954 --> 00:31:56.619 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Right.

00:31:56.619 --> 00:31:58.330 align:middle line:84%
And the issue is
there's a new science.

00:31:58.330 --> 00:32:00.960 align:middle line:84%
And it's actually not that
new, it's almost 100 years old.

00:32:00.960 --> 00:32:02.794 align:middle line:90%
And it's called quantum physics.

00:32:02.794 --> 00:32:03.960 align:middle line:90%
And what's the significance?

00:32:03.960 --> 00:32:06.370 align:middle line:84%
Quantum physics
completely turns the table

00:32:06.370 --> 00:32:08.490 align:middle line:84%
on Newtonian physics
for this reason.

00:32:08.490 --> 00:32:12.470 align:middle line:84%
It says, the primary controlling
influence in this universe

00:32:12.470 --> 00:32:15.770 align:middle line:84%
are the invisible
forces, the energy.

00:32:15.770 --> 00:32:19.120 align:middle line:84%
It's the energy that
shapes the material world.

00:32:19.120 --> 00:32:21.720 align:middle line:84%
And it's like
collectively, we talk

00:32:21.720 --> 00:32:23.180 align:middle line:90%
about all the energy in physics.

00:32:23.180 --> 00:32:24.950 align:middle line:90%
We call it the field.

00:32:24.950 --> 00:32:26.990 align:middle line:84%
Lynne McTaggart has a
great book on "The Field."

00:32:26.990 --> 00:32:27.698 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes.

00:32:27.698 --> 00:32:29.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And we say,
well, what's the field?

00:32:29.730 --> 00:32:31.960 align:middle line:84%
Well it's the invisible
forces that are around us.

00:32:31.960 --> 00:32:34.470 align:middle line:84%
And I say well, what does
quantum physics say about this?

00:32:34.470 --> 00:32:39.600 align:middle line:84%
It says look, the field is
the soul governing agency

00:32:39.600 --> 00:32:40.850 align:middle line:90%
of matter.

00:32:40.850 --> 00:32:43.160 align:middle line:84%
This is a quote from
Albert Einstein.

00:32:43.160 --> 00:32:44.520 align:middle line:90%
And what does it mean?

00:32:44.520 --> 00:32:47.340 align:middle line:84%
The soul governing agency
of the physical realm

00:32:47.340 --> 00:32:50.550 align:middle line:84%
is not the physical realm
but the invisible energy.

00:32:50.550 --> 00:32:52.796 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What's outside
of the physical realm.

00:32:52.796 --> 00:32:55.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, the physical
realm turns out to be energy

00:32:55.170 --> 00:32:55.760 align:middle line:90%
as well, so that's--

00:32:55.760 --> 00:32:56.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Same thing.

00:32:56.330 --> 00:32:57.180 align:middle line:90%
So it's-- I see.

00:32:57.180 --> 00:32:57.680 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:32:57.680 --> 00:33:00.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: You see, when
we took the atom apart--

00:33:00.400 --> 00:33:02.220 align:middle line:84%
and everybody's
seen this in school.

00:33:02.220 --> 00:33:04.430 align:middle line:84%
The atom looks like a little
solar system, marbles,

00:33:04.430 --> 00:33:06.439 align:middle line:84%
ball bearings moving
around, stuff like that.

00:33:06.439 --> 00:33:08.730 align:middle line:84%
When they went inside to look
at those things, protons,

00:33:08.730 --> 00:33:11.490 align:middle line:84%
electrons, neutrons, they said,
well what are they made out of?

00:33:11.490 --> 00:33:13.389 align:middle line:84%
That's where the big
surprise came from.

00:33:13.389 --> 00:33:15.180 align:middle line:84%
Because they said,
what's a proton made of?

00:33:15.180 --> 00:33:17.327 align:middle line:84%
It's like when they
looked inside, energy.

00:33:17.327 --> 00:33:18.660 align:middle line:90%
Electron, what's it made out of?

00:33:18.660 --> 00:33:19.190 align:middle line:90%
Energy.

00:33:19.190 --> 00:33:22.020 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, what
we perceive as physical

00:33:22.020 --> 00:33:23.381 align:middle line:90%
is just another form of energy.

00:33:23.381 --> 00:33:23.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:33:23.880 --> 00:33:26.140 align:middle line:84%
And that energy of
the physical body

00:33:26.140 --> 00:33:27.910 align:middle line:84%
is connected to the
energy of the field.

00:33:27.910 --> 00:33:30.020 align:middle line:84%
So as the energy of
the field changes,

00:33:30.020 --> 00:33:32.590 align:middle line:84%
it changes the energy
of our physical body.

00:33:32.590 --> 00:33:36.870 align:middle line:84%
And that's why the field is
considered the soul governing

00:33:36.870 --> 00:33:39.380 align:middle line:84%
agency of that particle
or material world.

00:33:39.380 --> 00:33:41.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's basically
really all interconnected.

00:33:41.790 --> 00:33:43.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Oh, that's
the whole idea.

00:33:43.290 --> 00:33:44.320 align:middle line:90%
There is no separation.

00:33:44.320 --> 00:33:46.390 align:middle line:84%
It's very interesting
because if you

00:33:46.390 --> 00:33:48.520 align:middle line:84%
ask me, well, give a
definition of the field.

00:33:48.520 --> 00:33:51.760 align:middle line:84%
And I would say, the field
represents invisible moving

00:33:51.760 --> 00:33:54.370 align:middle line:84%
forces that shape
the physical world.

00:33:54.370 --> 00:33:56.480 align:middle line:84%
And then I go, wow,
isn't that interesting.

00:33:56.480 --> 00:33:57.777 align:middle line:90%
There was a word spirit.

00:33:57.777 --> 00:33:59.610 align:middle line:84%
And I said, what's the
definition of spirit?

00:33:59.610 --> 00:34:03.330 align:middle line:84%
Invisible moving forces that
influence the physical world.

00:34:03.330 --> 00:34:05.750 align:middle line:84%
And so what's
really coming about

00:34:05.750 --> 00:34:08.050 align:middle line:84%
is a cycle that's
being completed.

00:34:08.050 --> 00:34:10.929 align:middle line:84%
We started off with an
awareness of spirituality,

00:34:10.929 --> 00:34:12.600 align:middle line:84%
but not really an
understanding of it,

00:34:12.600 --> 00:34:15.440 align:middle line:84%
but there was like that
mysterious invisible.

00:34:15.440 --> 00:34:17.150 align:middle line:84%
We went through a
whole history and what

00:34:17.150 --> 00:34:19.110 align:middle line:84%
does quantum physics
return us to?

00:34:19.110 --> 00:34:20.980 align:middle line:84%
It's, yes, there
is the equivalent

00:34:20.980 --> 00:34:23.710 align:middle line:84%
of that invisible
spiritual energy

00:34:23.710 --> 00:34:26.570 align:middle line:84%
and we also now
understand the mechanics.

00:34:26.570 --> 00:34:30.850 align:middle line:84%
And now all of a sudden, it
becomes scientific spirituality

00:34:30.850 --> 00:34:31.400 align:middle line:90%
in a sense.

00:34:31.400 --> 00:34:34.017 align:middle line:84%
It's like not mystical,
but it's part of our world.

00:34:34.017 --> 00:34:34.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see.

00:34:34.600 --> 00:34:38.829 align:middle line:84%
That's how the gap has been
bridged by what your work is.

00:34:38.829 --> 00:34:40.370 align:middle line:84%
Now, you mentioned
a few other myths.

00:34:40.370 --> 00:34:40.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Yeah.

00:34:40.580 --> 00:34:41.639 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You said
that there was four.

00:34:41.639 --> 00:34:43.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And the second
one is very critical.

00:34:43.070 --> 00:34:44.909 align:middle line:84%
And the second one
is that we've all

00:34:44.909 --> 00:34:47.560 align:middle line:84%
been programmed with the belief
that genes control our lives.

00:34:47.560 --> 00:34:48.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:34:48.110 --> 00:34:49.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: I say, well,
why is that relevant?

00:34:49.050 --> 00:34:50.690 align:middle line:84%
And I say, well,
as far as we know,

00:34:50.690 --> 00:34:52.810 align:middle line:84%
we didn't pick the
genes we came with.

00:34:52.810 --> 00:34:55.575 align:middle line:84%
The genes that we have, if we
don't like the physical traits

00:34:55.575 --> 00:34:57.200 align:middle line:84%
that they provide,
then we say, well, I

00:34:57.200 --> 00:34:58.325 align:middle line:90%
can't do anything about it.

00:34:58.325 --> 00:34:59.454 align:middle line:90%
I can't change the genes.

00:34:59.454 --> 00:35:02.120 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden you start to
realize, you say wait a minute.

00:35:02.120 --> 00:35:05.280 align:middle line:84%
Genes control my life and
as science tried to show us

00:35:05.280 --> 00:35:09.430 align:middle line:84%
it controls behavior, emotions,
and physical characteristics.

00:35:09.430 --> 00:35:11.920 align:middle line:84%
And then you realize but
you don't control the genes.

00:35:11.920 --> 00:35:13.900 align:middle line:84%
Then all of a sudden,
we've been put back

00:35:13.900 --> 00:35:16.610 align:middle line:84%
just like in the
previous civilization.

00:35:16.610 --> 00:35:19.780 align:middle line:84%
Monotheism says, look, you
don't-- are not connected

00:35:19.780 --> 00:35:20.980 align:middle line:90%
to spirit.

00:35:20.980 --> 00:35:22.830 align:middle line:84%
Now, you're not
connected to your genes.

00:35:22.830 --> 00:35:24.139 align:middle line:90%
You can't change your genes.

00:35:24.139 --> 00:35:26.180 align:middle line:84%
Well, then all of a sudden,
it says, oh, my gosh.

00:35:26.180 --> 00:35:28.620 align:middle line:90%
I'm a victim of my heredity.

00:35:28.620 --> 00:35:30.834 align:middle line:84%
If there's cancer or diabetes
running in my family--

00:35:30.834 --> 00:35:32.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I'm going to get it.

00:35:32.000 --> 00:35:32.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: -I'm going to get it.

00:35:32.710 --> 00:35:33.668 align:middle line:90%
What can I do about it?

00:35:33.668 --> 00:35:35.597 align:middle line:84%
Well, just like in the
previous civilization

00:35:35.597 --> 00:35:37.180 align:middle line:84%
when you find yourself
being a victim,

00:35:37.180 --> 00:35:39.840 align:middle line:90%
then you seek a rescuer.

00:35:39.840 --> 00:35:41.840 align:middle line:84%
So we go out there and
we look at the field

00:35:41.840 --> 00:35:44.850 align:middle line:84%
of allopathic medicine and say
look, I'm a victim of my genes.

00:35:44.850 --> 00:35:47.690 align:middle line:84%
What can you do to
help me overcome

00:35:47.690 --> 00:35:51.290 align:middle line:84%
the consequence of my genes and
what's running in my family?

00:35:51.290 --> 00:35:53.610 align:middle line:90%
Well, new science.

00:35:53.610 --> 00:35:54.890 align:middle line:90%
Genes-- yes, go ahead.

00:35:54.890 --> 00:35:56.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's so interesting,
it's the first thing that you

00:35:56.140 --> 00:35:58.139 align:middle line:84%
write down when you go
into a doctor's office is

00:35:58.139 --> 00:36:01.355 align:middle line:84%
your genetic history, as if
it is a blueprint for you.

00:36:01.355 --> 00:36:01.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Yeah.

00:36:01.980 --> 00:36:04.900 align:middle line:84%
And this is the biggest error
because since we believe

00:36:04.900 --> 00:36:08.010 align:middle line:84%
that that family lineage is
what's passing on the trait

00:36:08.010 --> 00:36:11.550 align:middle line:84%
and we believe that all traits
are controlled by genes, then

00:36:11.550 --> 00:36:14.820 align:middle line:84%
we don't really care
about the psychology

00:36:14.820 --> 00:36:16.330 align:middle line:84%
or what was going
on in the culture.

00:36:16.330 --> 00:36:17.080 align:middle line:90%
That's irrelevant.

00:36:17.080 --> 00:36:18.020 align:middle line:90%
You are genes.

00:36:18.020 --> 00:36:20.262 align:middle line:84%
You're manifesting
gene expression.

00:36:20.262 --> 00:36:22.220 align:middle line:84%
That takes you out of
the picture again, right?

00:36:22.220 --> 00:36:24.930 align:middle line:84%
But now we're beginning to
know a whole new understanding.

00:36:24.930 --> 00:36:26.500 align:middle line:90%
There's a whole new science.

00:36:26.500 --> 00:36:28.760 align:middle line:84%
Genetics, the
belief of genetics--

00:36:28.760 --> 00:36:31.210 align:middle line:84%
let's just make a
simple flat statement.

00:36:31.210 --> 00:36:34.624 align:middle line:90%
Genes control nothing.

00:36:34.624 --> 00:36:35.790 align:middle line:90%
They don't control anything.

00:36:35.790 --> 00:36:38.320 align:middle line:84%
Genes-- and we heard in
school and we all-- you go out

00:36:38.320 --> 00:36:39.430 align:middle line:84%
and talk to the average
person on the street.

00:36:39.430 --> 00:36:41.805 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That breaks every
single belief system out there.

00:36:41.805 --> 00:36:44.172 align:middle line:84%
It breaks all scientific
facts right now.

00:36:44.172 --> 00:36:45.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well,
and it's profoundly

00:36:45.630 --> 00:36:46.879 align:middle line:90%
important for a simple reason.

00:36:46.879 --> 00:36:49.930 align:middle line:84%
Because if genes did control it
and we didn't pick the genes,

00:36:49.930 --> 00:36:53.270 align:middle line:84%
then by definition
we're out of control.

00:36:53.270 --> 00:36:56.600 align:middle line:84%
And so significantly,
there's a new science.

00:36:56.600 --> 00:36:58.470 align:middle line:84%
And let's just go
back for a sample

00:36:58.470 --> 00:37:00.780 align:middle line:84%
because how many times
have-- people talk every day.

00:37:00.780 --> 00:37:03.910 align:middle line:84%
Oh, a gene turned on,
a gene turned off,

00:37:03.910 --> 00:37:06.000 align:middle line:90%
a gene caused cancer.

00:37:06.000 --> 00:37:09.070 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out
those statements

00:37:09.070 --> 00:37:12.210 align:middle line:84%
are completely
false for a reason.

00:37:12.210 --> 00:37:14.010 align:middle line:90%
Genes are blueprints.

00:37:14.010 --> 00:37:16.700 align:middle line:84%
They're blueprints to make
the physical proteins that

00:37:16.700 --> 00:37:17.550 align:middle line:90%
give us our body.

00:37:17.550 --> 00:37:20.490 align:middle line:84%
And you say, well, yes they are
connected to our expression,

00:37:20.490 --> 00:37:22.240 align:middle line:84%
but do they control
the expression?

00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:23.720 align:middle line:90%
The answer is no.

00:37:23.720 --> 00:37:25.800 align:middle line:84%
Genes have no on and
genes have no off.

00:37:25.800 --> 00:37:27.250 align:middle line:90%
They're blueprints.

00:37:27.250 --> 00:37:31.465 align:middle line:84%
I love to put it in regard to,
look, if genes are blueprints,

00:37:31.465 --> 00:37:33.340 align:middle line:84%
think about it going to
an architect's office

00:37:33.340 --> 00:37:35.010 align:middle line:84%
and she's working
on a blueprint.

00:37:35.010 --> 00:37:36.593 align:middle line:84%
And you look over
her shoulder and you

00:37:36.593 --> 00:37:38.477 align:middle line:90%
say is your blueprint on or off?

00:37:38.477 --> 00:37:40.560 align:middle line:84%
And she'd looked at you
like, what are you, crazy?

00:37:40.560 --> 00:37:41.520 align:middle line:90%
There's no on and off.

00:37:41.520 --> 00:37:43.750 align:middle line:90%
And I go, precisely.

00:37:43.750 --> 00:37:47.960 align:middle line:84%
Genes are blueprints, but
they have no on, no off.

00:37:47.960 --> 00:37:49.590 align:middle line:84%
They don't have any
idea what's going

00:37:49.590 --> 00:37:51.550 align:middle line:90%
on in the world around them.

00:37:51.550 --> 00:37:53.160 align:middle line:90%
They're just blueprints.

00:37:53.160 --> 00:37:57.010 align:middle line:84%
We've been focusing on the
genes as being self-actualizing.

00:37:57.010 --> 00:37:58.570 align:middle line:90%
A gene makes a decision.

00:37:58.570 --> 00:38:01.930 align:middle line:84%
It turns out, absolutely
totally false.

00:38:01.930 --> 00:38:03.750 align:middle line:90%
A gene is a blueprint.

00:38:03.750 --> 00:38:05.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So a gene
cannot-- if someone, say,

00:38:05.590 --> 00:38:08.770 align:middle line:84%
has a cancer gene, it doesn't
automatically turn itself

00:38:08.770 --> 00:38:10.719 align:middle line:84%
on and express itself
as being cancer?

00:38:10.719 --> 00:38:11.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: No.

00:38:11.260 --> 00:38:11.750 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:38:11.750 --> 00:38:13.550 align:middle line:84%
The concept of a cancer
gene is totally misleading,

00:38:13.550 --> 00:38:15.780 align:middle line:84%
because if I said I had a
gene that causes cancer,

00:38:15.780 --> 00:38:18.610 align:middle line:84%
then if I had that gene then
anybody who has that gene

00:38:18.610 --> 00:38:19.594 align:middle line:90%
should have cancer.

00:38:19.594 --> 00:38:21.260 align:middle line:84%
And you say, well, I
have a cancer gene,

00:38:21.260 --> 00:38:23.290 align:middle line:84%
and 67% of the
people have cancer.

00:38:23.290 --> 00:38:24.910 align:middle line:90%
And I go, yeah, really cool.

00:38:24.910 --> 00:38:27.794 align:middle line:84%
What about the 33% that
have the gene and they

00:38:27.794 --> 00:38:28.710 align:middle line:90%
don't have the cancer?

00:38:28.710 --> 00:38:29.452 align:middle line:90%
Explain that.

00:38:29.452 --> 00:38:30.910 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
it's like, oh,

00:38:30.910 --> 00:38:32.130 align:middle line:84%
we don't want to
talk about that.

00:38:32.130 --> 00:38:33.360 align:middle line:84%
And I say, well I don't care
if you want to talk about it

00:38:33.360 --> 00:38:33.900 align:middle line:90%
or not.

00:38:33.900 --> 00:38:35.990 align:middle line:84%
They have the gene, they
don't have the cancer.

00:38:35.990 --> 00:38:37.000 align:middle line:90%
You tell me why.

00:38:37.000 --> 00:38:38.487 align:middle line:90%
Because that's the new biology.

00:38:38.487 --> 00:38:40.320 align:middle line:84%
The new biology is not
asking about the ones

00:38:40.320 --> 00:38:40.895 align:middle line:90%
that have the cancer.

00:38:40.895 --> 00:38:42.616 align:middle line:84%
It really wants to know
how can you have the gene

00:38:42.616 --> 00:38:43.820 align:middle line:90%
and not have the cancer?

00:38:43.820 --> 00:38:47.410 align:middle line:84%
So it turns out
genes are blueprints,

00:38:47.410 --> 00:38:50.970 align:middle line:84%
but there's a contractor in
the body, a contractor that

00:38:50.970 --> 00:38:53.660 align:middle line:84%
selects the blueprints
and can modify

00:38:53.660 --> 00:38:57.080 align:middle line:84%
the blueprints by their
response to the environment.

00:38:57.080 --> 00:39:01.330 align:middle line:84%
You adjust your genetics by how
you respond to the environment.

00:39:01.330 --> 00:39:03.390 align:middle line:90%
Is nature's intelligence.

00:39:03.390 --> 00:39:07.040 align:middle line:84%
If my genes were prefixed
and the environment changed

00:39:07.040 --> 00:39:09.720 align:middle line:84%
and my genes didn't fit,
then the whole species

00:39:09.720 --> 00:39:10.740 align:middle line:90%
would die out.

00:39:10.740 --> 00:39:12.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that's
what epigenetics is.

00:39:12.390 --> 00:39:13.056 align:middle line:90%
Epigenetics is--

00:39:13.056 --> 00:39:15.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: The new
science, epigenetics.

00:39:15.050 --> 00:39:17.207 align:middle line:84%
And it sounds like
the original science

00:39:17.207 --> 00:39:19.040 align:middle line:84%
that almost everybody
out there in the world

00:39:19.040 --> 00:39:21.740 align:middle line:84%
has learned, it's call
genetics or genetic control,

00:39:21.740 --> 00:39:24.280 align:middle line:90%
which means control by genes.

00:39:24.280 --> 00:39:26.230 align:middle line:84%
The new science almost
sounds the same.

00:39:26.230 --> 00:39:29.930 align:middle line:84%
It's called epigenetics
or epigenetic control.

00:39:29.930 --> 00:39:32.410 align:middle line:84%
What you have to catch
is that little epi part.

00:39:32.410 --> 00:39:34.180 align:middle line:90%
Epi means above.

00:39:34.180 --> 00:39:37.900 align:middle line:84%
So we say the word
for skin is epidermis.

00:39:37.900 --> 00:39:39.530 align:middle line:90%
I say, what is epidermis?

00:39:39.530 --> 00:39:41.770 align:middle line:84%
Dermis is the layer
below the skin.

00:39:41.770 --> 00:39:44.840 align:middle line:84%
Epidermis is the layer
above the dermis, the skin.

00:39:44.840 --> 00:39:45.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:39:45.340 --> 00:39:46.548 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: So epi means above.

00:39:46.548 --> 00:39:48.310 align:middle line:84%
So I say, what is
epigenetic control mean?

00:39:48.310 --> 00:39:52.040 align:middle line:90%
I go, control above the genes.

00:39:52.040 --> 00:39:54.520 align:middle line:84%
And now we start
to recognize how

00:39:54.520 --> 00:39:59.510 align:middle line:84%
the environment and our
perception of the environment

00:39:59.510 --> 00:40:02.010 align:middle line:84%
are responsible, not
for just selecting

00:40:02.010 --> 00:40:04.720 align:middle line:84%
the genes-- this fact I'm
going to say right now

00:40:04.720 --> 00:40:06.410 align:middle line:90%
is mind blowing.

00:40:06.410 --> 00:40:09.420 align:middle line:84%
How we perceive or
respond to the environment

00:40:09.420 --> 00:40:12.160 align:middle line:84%
can take every gene
blueprint that we have

00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:15.490 align:middle line:84%
and create thousands of
variations of proteins

00:40:15.490 --> 00:40:17.040 align:middle line:90%
from the same blueprint.

00:40:17.040 --> 00:40:19.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it
completely can change

00:40:19.010 --> 00:40:21.700 align:middle line:84%
based on the environment,
and the environment

00:40:21.700 --> 00:40:25.830 align:middle line:84%
being your upbringing,
your thoughts, your health,

00:40:25.830 --> 00:40:27.580 align:middle line:84%
your food, all of that
is the environment.

00:40:27.580 --> 00:40:29.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: All of
that is part of it.

00:40:29.240 --> 00:40:32.330 align:middle line:84%
And this is so empowering
for a very simple reason.

00:40:32.330 --> 00:40:33.949 align:middle line:84%
Genetic control,
I'm a victim, why?

00:40:33.949 --> 00:40:35.615 align:middle line:84%
I didn't pick them,
I can't change them,

00:40:35.615 --> 00:40:36.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm stuck with them.

00:40:36.530 --> 00:40:38.870 align:middle line:90%
Epigenetics says, no.

00:40:38.870 --> 00:40:40.950 align:middle line:84%
If you change the way
you respond to the world,

00:40:40.950 --> 00:40:42.740 align:middle line:90%
you change your genetic readout.

00:40:42.740 --> 00:40:44.410 align:middle line:90%
So, give you an example.

00:40:44.410 --> 00:40:48.690 align:middle line:84%
Only 10% of cancer
is heredity based.

00:40:48.690 --> 00:40:53.110 align:middle line:84%
90% of cancer are people
responding inappropriately

00:40:53.110 --> 00:40:55.160 align:middle line:84%
to the environment
and then creating

00:40:55.160 --> 00:40:58.560 align:middle line:84%
a variation on their genes
that leads to the cancer.

00:40:58.560 --> 00:41:01.100 align:middle line:84%
They didn't have an
inherent cancer gene.

00:41:01.100 --> 00:41:03.701 align:middle line:84%
They modified the
readout of their genes.

00:41:03.701 --> 00:41:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course, then
there's the flip side.

00:41:05.700 --> 00:41:08.830 align:middle line:84%
And the flip side is somebody
who has a terminal cancer

00:41:08.830 --> 00:41:12.020 align:middle line:84%
but changes their
perception or response

00:41:12.020 --> 00:41:13.870 align:middle line:84%
to the world around
them, and then

00:41:13.870 --> 00:41:16.660 align:middle line:84%
has what we call a
spontaneous remission.

00:41:16.660 --> 00:41:18.490 align:middle line:90%
And that's not a miracle.

00:41:18.490 --> 00:41:20.600 align:middle line:84%
It's just the fact
that you have changed

00:41:20.600 --> 00:41:23.600 align:middle line:84%
the relationship between
your perception and the genes

00:41:23.600 --> 00:41:24.855 align:middle line:90%
and you can rewrite the genes.

00:41:24.855 --> 00:41:26.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And we're going
to speak specifically

00:41:26.730 --> 00:41:28.460 align:middle line:84%
about what that has
to do with stress,

00:41:28.460 --> 00:41:31.770 align:middle line:84%
and how you can change
your response to stress

00:41:31.770 --> 00:41:34.770 align:middle line:84%
and your perception
of stress and not

00:41:34.770 --> 00:41:37.237 align:middle line:84%
activate the genetic
marker for cancer.

00:41:37.237 --> 00:41:38.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: That's the whole idea.

00:41:38.570 --> 00:41:40.440 align:middle line:84%
We are so empowered,
and yet, we've

00:41:40.440 --> 00:41:42.470 align:middle line:84%
been programmed to believe
that we're victims.

00:41:42.470 --> 00:41:44.970 align:middle line:84%
And since perception
controls, if you

00:41:44.970 --> 00:41:48.326 align:middle line:84%
perceive you are a
victim, that perception

00:41:48.326 --> 00:41:50.704 align:middle line:90%
will manifest as expression.

00:41:50.704 --> 00:41:52.370 align:middle line:84%
There is a simple
quote from Henry Ford.

00:41:52.370 --> 00:41:55.730 align:middle line:84%
He says, if you
believe you can or you

00:41:55.730 --> 00:41:57.780 align:middle line:90%
believe you can't, you're right.

00:41:57.780 --> 00:41:59.845 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I have a
shirt with that, yes.

00:41:59.845 --> 00:42:00.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Yeah.

00:42:00.470 --> 00:42:02.567 align:middle line:84%
So there's just two
more beliefs and then

00:42:02.567 --> 00:42:03.775 align:middle line:90%
we can go through these four.

00:42:03.775 --> 00:42:04.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK, go ahead.

00:42:04.250 --> 00:42:04.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: OK.

00:42:04.880 --> 00:42:09.890 align:middle line:84%
The third belief is the belief
that the world is really

00:42:09.890 --> 00:42:12.060 align:middle line:84%
a Darwinian world
and that we're here

00:42:12.060 --> 00:42:15.420 align:middle line:84%
on a competition for fitness
and survival in that world.

00:42:15.420 --> 00:42:18.470 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out the
evolution of the planet

00:42:18.470 --> 00:42:20.100 align:middle line:90%
is not a competition.

00:42:20.100 --> 00:42:22.866 align:middle line:84%
We referred once to that
there was a garden here.

00:42:22.866 --> 00:42:24.740 align:middle line:84%
And if you understand
the nature of a garden,

00:42:24.740 --> 00:42:27.410 align:middle line:84%
a garden is not an
expression of competition.

00:42:27.410 --> 00:42:30.880 align:middle line:84%
A garden is an expression
of total cooperation.

00:42:30.880 --> 00:42:33.250 align:middle line:84%
And so the reality is what
happened to the garden?

00:42:33.250 --> 00:42:35.990 align:middle line:84%
The answer is once
we put in competition

00:42:35.990 --> 00:42:37.370 align:middle line:90%
instead of cooperation--

00:42:37.370 --> 00:42:38.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Our pesticides and--

00:42:38.780 --> 00:42:39.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: -and everything.

00:42:39.350 --> 00:42:40.740 align:middle line:84%
We destroy them because
we're going to say, look,

00:42:40.740 --> 00:42:42.240 align:middle line:84%
we don't want to
cooperate with you.

00:42:42.240 --> 00:42:44.200 align:middle line:84%
We want you to do what
we want you to do.

00:42:44.200 --> 00:42:48.790 align:middle line:84%
So human domination of nature
has been the whole concept

00:42:48.790 --> 00:42:50.450 align:middle line:84%
that science could
dominate nature.

00:42:50.450 --> 00:42:53.640 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, no,
I don't think so.

00:42:53.640 --> 00:42:56.090 align:middle line:84%
The reality is our
meddling with nature

00:42:56.090 --> 00:43:01.080 align:middle line:84%
is actually responsible for the
looming extinction right now.

00:43:01.080 --> 00:43:02.970 align:middle line:90%
So there's a new understanding.

00:43:02.970 --> 00:43:06.090 align:middle line:84%
It's not the survival
of the fittest.

00:43:06.090 --> 00:43:08.130 align:middle line:84%
I created a new
word, fittingest.

00:43:08.130 --> 00:43:09.680 align:middle line:84%
It's a survival
of the fittingest,

00:43:09.680 --> 00:43:13.790 align:middle line:84%
meaning those organisms that
cooperate with the garden are

00:43:13.790 --> 00:43:15.640 align:middle line:84%
going to be encouraged
by the garden

00:43:15.640 --> 00:43:18.390 align:middle line:84%
to maintain its
existence on the planet.

00:43:18.390 --> 00:43:20.750 align:middle line:84%
Those organisms
that are actually

00:43:20.750 --> 00:43:23.240 align:middle line:84%
competing with the
garden or interfering

00:43:23.240 --> 00:43:25.060 align:middle line:84%
with the garden,
nature will tend

00:43:25.060 --> 00:43:27.050 align:middle line:84%
to eliminate those
organisms over time.

00:43:27.050 --> 00:43:27.925 align:middle line:90%
They will go extinct.

00:43:27.925 --> 00:43:29.591 align:middle line:84%
And then you look at
human civilization,

00:43:29.591 --> 00:43:31.270 align:middle line:84%
and you go, yeah,
nature's not really

00:43:31.270 --> 00:43:33.175 align:middle line:84%
pretty happy with
the destruction

00:43:33.175 --> 00:43:34.050 align:middle line:90%
that we have wrought.

00:43:34.050 --> 00:43:37.420 align:middle line:84%
So we're sort of like fleas on
the back of nature right now,

00:43:37.420 --> 00:43:39.410 align:middle line:84%
and she's trying
to shake us off.

00:43:39.410 --> 00:43:41.865 align:middle line:84%
And the issue is either we
learn to work with her--

00:43:41.865 --> 00:43:43.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In cooperation, yes.

00:43:43.280 --> 00:43:46.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: -or nature's going
to be here, we'll just be gone.

00:43:46.330 --> 00:43:47.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All right.

00:43:47.080 --> 00:43:48.920 align:middle line:84%
So you mentioned that
there were four myths.

00:43:48.920 --> 00:43:49.667 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: OK.

00:43:49.667 --> 00:43:50.750 align:middle line:90%
And we have one more left.

00:43:50.750 --> 00:43:51.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:43:51.250 --> 00:43:53.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And the fourth
one is the concept

00:43:53.180 --> 00:43:54.890 align:middle line:84%
that evolution is
a random process.

00:43:54.890 --> 00:43:57.860 align:middle line:84%
This is the belief
in Darwinian theory

00:43:57.860 --> 00:43:59.930 align:middle line:84%
that the mutations that
kick everything off

00:43:59.930 --> 00:44:03.450 align:middle line:84%
are called random mutations,
genetic accidents.

00:44:03.450 --> 00:44:05.200 align:middle line:84%
The significance of
that is if we got here

00:44:05.200 --> 00:44:07.980 align:middle line:84%
through random mutations, you
might say then why are we here?

00:44:07.980 --> 00:44:09.980 align:middle line:84%
And then I have to say,
it was just an accident.

00:44:09.980 --> 00:44:11.900 align:middle line:84%
It was just shaking
genetic dice.

00:44:11.900 --> 00:44:14.480 align:middle line:84%
If a mutation would have
gone left instead of right

00:44:14.480 --> 00:44:17.740 align:middle line:84%
a million years ago, maybe
we wouldn't be here today.

00:44:17.740 --> 00:44:19.190 align:middle line:90%
That's the belief.

00:44:19.190 --> 00:44:20.980 align:middle line:84%
The new belief
reveals, no, it's not

00:44:20.980 --> 00:44:24.649 align:middle line:84%
random mutations that really
provided for our existence,

00:44:24.649 --> 00:44:25.440 align:middle line:90%
it's something new.

00:44:25.440 --> 00:44:27.700 align:middle line:84%
It's called an
adaptive mutation.

00:44:27.700 --> 00:44:29.220 align:middle line:84%
And what it really
means is this,

00:44:29.220 --> 00:44:32.400 align:middle line:84%
is that we and every
other organism that

00:44:32.400 --> 00:44:37.470 align:middle line:84%
is in this environment got
here as part of an effort

00:44:37.470 --> 00:44:41.376 align:middle line:84%
to adapt and conform and
support the environment,

00:44:41.376 --> 00:44:42.500 align:middle line:90%
the garden in that we live.

00:44:42.500 --> 00:44:43.375 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Explain that.

00:44:43.375 --> 00:44:46.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: So it basically
says when an organism comes

00:44:46.190 --> 00:44:48.940 align:middle line:84%
into an environment,
it has a tendency

00:44:48.940 --> 00:44:50.060 align:middle line:90%
to alter the environment.

00:44:50.060 --> 00:44:50.810 align:middle line:90%
It's going to eat.

00:44:50.810 --> 00:44:53.020 align:middle line:84%
It's going to leave
waste materials behind.

00:44:53.020 --> 00:44:54.980 align:middle line:84%
It's going to alter
the environment.

00:44:54.980 --> 00:44:58.180 align:middle line:84%
Well, the idea if I bring in
an organism to create harmony

00:44:58.180 --> 00:45:01.150 align:middle line:84%
and then at some point
it gets out of balance,

00:45:01.150 --> 00:45:03.950 align:middle line:84%
nature introduces
another organism

00:45:03.950 --> 00:45:06.920 align:middle line:84%
that will then try to
rebalance it again.

00:45:06.920 --> 00:45:10.210 align:middle line:84%
And so a new organism
comes in to compensate

00:45:10.210 --> 00:45:12.850 align:middle line:84%
for the previous organism,
but then ultimately this one

00:45:12.850 --> 00:45:16.090 align:middle line:84%
may throw it out of balance so
another organism is introduced.

00:45:16.090 --> 00:45:18.710 align:middle line:84%
You keep adding organisms to
create harmony and balance.

00:45:18.710 --> 00:45:20.680 align:middle line:84%
And every time you
add an organism,

00:45:20.680 --> 00:45:22.810 align:middle line:84%
it has more power and
influence in creating

00:45:22.810 --> 00:45:23.852 align:middle line:90%
harmony and balance.

00:45:23.852 --> 00:45:25.310 align:middle line:84%
And you say, OK,
what about humans?

00:45:25.310 --> 00:45:28.054 align:middle line:84%
Well, we're near the top
of this one after the other

00:45:28.054 --> 00:45:28.720 align:middle line:90%
after the other.

00:45:28.720 --> 00:45:33.720 align:middle line:84%
And being near the top,
we have so much power

00:45:33.720 --> 00:45:36.150 align:middle line:84%
in altering or
influencing environment

00:45:36.150 --> 00:45:39.270 align:middle line:84%
that without knowledge
of our effort of trying

00:45:39.270 --> 00:45:42.790 align:middle line:84%
to keep harmony in the garden,
the same powers that we have,

00:45:42.790 --> 00:45:45.730 align:middle line:84%
have led to the current state
of destroying the garden.

00:45:45.730 --> 00:45:47.527 align:middle line:84%
And so it's really
the fact is no, no.

00:45:47.527 --> 00:45:49.610 align:middle line:84%
We have to recognize we
didn't get here by action,

00:45:49.610 --> 00:45:52.840 align:middle line:84%
we actually have a job and
that is to tend the garden.

00:45:52.840 --> 00:45:53.910 align:middle line:90%
So it's interesting--

00:45:53.910 --> 00:45:54.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To get ourselves
out of it, yes.

00:45:54.960 --> 00:45:56.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: The new
civilization ultimately

00:45:56.970 --> 00:46:01.190 align:middle line:84%
comes back in a circle back
to the original animus, who

00:46:01.190 --> 00:46:05.100 align:middle line:84%
were spiritual and material,
and also as the Native Americans

00:46:05.100 --> 00:46:07.460 align:middle line:84%
said, we are here
to tend the garden,

00:46:07.460 --> 00:46:09.150 align:middle line:90%
and we've lost that mission.

00:46:09.150 --> 00:46:11.600 align:middle line:84%
And as a result, the
looming extinction

00:46:11.600 --> 00:46:14.010 align:middle line:84%
is an expression of
we're out of balance.

00:46:14.010 --> 00:46:15.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we are
here now to tend

00:46:15.460 --> 00:46:19.810 align:middle line:84%
our own environmental garden of
our thoughts, our surroundings,

00:46:19.810 --> 00:46:23.280 align:middle line:84%
our environment in order
to positively impact

00:46:23.280 --> 00:46:24.615 align:middle line:90%
our own genes, right?

00:46:24.615 --> 00:46:25.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely.

00:46:25.490 --> 00:46:28.230 align:middle line:84%
Old hippie statement, before
you go out and change the world,

00:46:28.230 --> 00:46:29.730 align:middle line:90%
take care of your backyard.

00:46:29.730 --> 00:46:31.710 align:middle line:84%
And I think when we
come back, basically--

00:46:31.710 --> 00:46:33.802 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Old hippie statement.

00:46:33.802 --> 00:46:35.660 align:middle line:90%
Very profound.

00:46:35.660 --> 00:46:37.596 align:middle line:90%
Old hippie statement.

00:46:37.596 --> 00:46:38.860 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:46:38.860 --> 00:46:39.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: We're going
to come back and learn

00:46:39.780 --> 00:46:42.250 align:middle line:84%
that before we can go out there
and evolve with the world,

00:46:42.250 --> 00:46:44.190 align:middle line:84%
we first have to
recognize who we are

00:46:44.190 --> 00:46:46.760 align:middle line:84%
and evolve ourselves
so that we become

00:46:46.760 --> 00:46:48.961 align:middle line:84%
a contributing element
to a future civilization.

00:46:48.961 --> 00:46:49.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:46:49.460 --> 00:46:51.876 align:middle line:84%
And this is really-- we're
going to cover the how on this,

00:46:51.876 --> 00:46:54.635 align:middle line:84%
exactly how the cells do
respond to the environment.

00:46:54.635 --> 00:46:56.980 align:middle line:84%
We're going to see that
through Petri dish slides.

00:46:56.980 --> 00:46:59.726 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I meant by
this information could radically

00:46:59.726 --> 00:47:01.350 align:middle line:84%
change the way that
you live your life.

00:47:01.350 --> 00:47:03.550 align:middle line:84%
When you really
truly see the impact

00:47:03.550 --> 00:47:05.490 align:middle line:84%
of your thoughts and
positive thoughts

00:47:05.490 --> 00:47:07.350 align:middle line:84%
and our perception
of those thoughts

00:47:07.350 --> 00:47:09.460 align:middle line:84%
on the growth of
the cell, you'll

00:47:09.460 --> 00:47:12.737 align:middle line:84%
understand what it means to
have those positive thoughts.

