01:20:48.740 --> 01:20:49.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

01:20:49.020 --> 01:20:50.603 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: So I go,
that's really cool.

01:20:50.603 --> 01:20:53.477 align:middle line:84%
And I say, OK, conscious mind
is you, creativity, et cetera.

01:20:53.477 --> 01:20:55.310 align:middle line:84%
And I say, what about
the subconscious mind?

01:20:55.310 --> 01:20:57.130 align:middle line:84%
You go, oh, that's
the rest of the brain

01:20:57.130 --> 01:20:58.590 align:middle line:84%
besides that little
frontal piece.

01:20:58.590 --> 01:21:00.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's an
enormous amount.

01:21:00.240 --> 01:21:01.614 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Yeah,
because the brain

01:21:01.614 --> 01:21:03.350 align:middle line:84%
was evolved before
consciousness evolved.

01:21:03.350 --> 01:21:05.760 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- so consciousness
was an add on more or less.

01:21:05.760 --> 01:21:07.390 align:middle line:84%
And interesting as
an add on option,

01:21:07.390 --> 01:21:08.640 align:middle line:90%
most people don't even use it.

01:21:08.640 --> 01:21:12.797 align:middle line:84%
But the subconscious is
essentially the whole brain.

01:21:12.797 --> 01:21:14.380 align:middle line:84%
I say, well, what
is the subconscious?

01:21:14.380 --> 01:21:17.320 align:middle line:84%
Oh, It's more like a
record playback device.

01:21:17.320 --> 01:21:21.174 align:middle line:84%
It records your experiences, and
then at the push of a button,

01:21:21.174 --> 01:21:22.090 align:middle line:90%
it can play them back.

01:21:22.090 --> 01:21:23.631 align:middle line:84%
And every time you
push it back, it's

01:21:23.631 --> 01:21:25.130 align:middle line:90%
a very accurate recording thing.

01:21:25.130 --> 01:21:26.630 align:middle line:84%
So every time you
push it back, it's

01:21:26.630 --> 01:21:29.980 align:middle line:84%
going to play the same thing
over and over and over again.

01:21:29.980 --> 01:21:32.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And all this is
imprinted in the first seven

01:21:32.180 --> 01:21:33.330 align:middle line:90%
years of your life, right?

01:21:33.330 --> 01:21:35.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, the fundamental
beliefs are put into it

01:21:35.760 --> 01:21:40.050 align:middle line:84%
and so it's a habitual mind,
but the first habits are really

01:21:40.050 --> 01:21:43.550 align:middle line:84%
acquired from your instincts
and your experiences.

01:21:43.550 --> 01:21:46.190 align:middle line:84%
And so here-- what
we now know is this.

01:21:46.190 --> 01:21:49.180 align:middle line:84%
The first six years of
your life, your brain's

01:21:49.180 --> 01:21:51.010 align:middle line:84%
not even operating at
the conscious level.

01:21:51.010 --> 01:21:54.840 align:middle line:84%
Its EEG, the predominant
brain state, is called theta.

01:21:54.840 --> 01:21:56.910 align:middle line:84%
Alpha, the next higher
level is consciousness.

01:21:56.910 --> 01:21:59.450 align:middle line:84%
Theta is just below
consciousness.

01:21:59.450 --> 01:22:01.300 align:middle line:90%
It's a state of imagination.

01:22:01.300 --> 01:22:04.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's where kids are from
especially between two and six.

01:22:04.010 --> 01:22:04.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:22:04.510 --> 01:22:06.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: They mix the
imaginary and the real world.

01:22:06.600 --> 01:22:07.099 align:middle line:90%
Why?

01:22:07.099 --> 01:22:10.370 align:middle line:84%
Their brain is operating at a
level of theta, imagination.

01:22:10.370 --> 01:22:13.820 align:middle line:84%
But it's also this
brain state of hypnosis.

01:22:13.820 --> 01:22:15.410 align:middle line:90%
What it means is this.

01:22:15.410 --> 01:22:16.910 align:middle line:84%
The first six
years of your life,

01:22:16.910 --> 01:22:19.780 align:middle line:84%
you're not really conscious,
you're in a state of hypnosis.

01:22:19.780 --> 01:22:22.942 align:middle line:84%
You observe everyone around you,
specifically your parents first

01:22:22.942 --> 01:22:24.400 align:middle line:84%
and then your family
and community.

01:22:24.400 --> 01:22:25.670 align:middle line:90%
What are you observing?

01:22:25.670 --> 01:22:27.750 align:middle line:84%
You're observing their
behaviors and you're

01:22:27.750 --> 01:22:30.940 align:middle line:84%
downloading their behaviors
and their responses.

01:22:30.940 --> 01:22:32.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's not what you
say, it's what you do.

01:22:32.940 --> 01:22:33.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: And that's the issue.

01:22:33.780 --> 01:22:36.570 align:middle line:84%
And that's why parents don't
realize, every move they make,

01:22:36.570 --> 01:22:39.330 align:middle line:84%
the child is like the
record button is on.

01:22:39.330 --> 01:22:40.870 align:middle line:90%
It's not off, it's on.

01:22:40.870 --> 01:22:43.530 align:middle line:84%
So everything that the
parents are doing is recorded.

01:22:43.530 --> 01:22:48.150 align:middle line:84%
So the first programs in
your subconscious mind

01:22:48.150 --> 01:22:49.080 align:middle line:90%
are not even yours.

01:22:49.080 --> 01:22:52.410 align:middle line:84%
They're acquired by downloading
other people's beliefs.

01:22:52.410 --> 01:22:55.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So all of my
relationship to everything

01:22:55.190 --> 01:22:57.710 align:middle line:90%
is being recorded by my child?

01:22:57.710 --> 01:22:59.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: By your
child, absolutely.

01:22:59.240 --> 01:23:03.050 align:middle line:84%
And this is not a new thing
because the Jesuits were

01:23:03.050 --> 01:23:05.270 align:middle line:84%
very proud of the fact that
they say, give me a child

01:23:05.270 --> 01:23:06.730 align:middle line:90%
and I will show you the man.

01:23:06.730 --> 01:23:08.190 align:middle line:84%
What do they know
is if I can get

01:23:08.190 --> 01:23:10.600 align:middle line:84%
the programming
of the child, then

01:23:10.600 --> 01:23:12.390 align:middle line:84%
I will control the
outcome of that person.

01:23:12.390 --> 01:23:14.352 align:middle line:84%
Or they would sometimes
say, give me a child

01:23:14.352 --> 01:23:15.810 align:middle line:84%
until it's six or
seven and it will

01:23:15.810 --> 01:23:17.880 align:middle line:84%
belong to the church for
the rest of its life.

01:23:17.880 --> 01:23:20.980 align:middle line:84%
What they knew is that
if I can instill a belief

01:23:20.980 --> 01:23:24.117 align:middle line:84%
system in there before
seven years of age,

01:23:24.117 --> 01:23:26.200 align:middle line:84%
then that belief system
is going to be fundamental

01:23:26.200 --> 01:23:27.870 align:middle line:90%
in the subconscious, OK?

01:23:27.870 --> 01:23:29.540 align:middle line:84%
So now here's the
issue that most people

01:23:29.540 --> 01:23:30.560 align:middle line:90%
have a problem with.

01:23:30.560 --> 01:23:31.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:23:31.060 --> 01:23:32.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Most of us walk
down the street saying,

01:23:32.430 --> 01:23:34.221 align:middle line:84%
yes, I'm controlling
my life with my wishes

01:23:34.221 --> 01:23:36.560 align:middle line:84%
and my desires, my
positive thinking.

01:23:36.560 --> 01:23:38.900 align:middle line:84%
And I go, that's really
cool except science

01:23:38.900 --> 01:23:41.090 align:middle line:84%
has revealed that
that's not true at all.

01:23:41.090 --> 01:23:45.240 align:middle line:84%
Science has revealed that
we operate 5% of the time

01:23:45.240 --> 01:23:47.870 align:middle line:84%
from our conscious
mind, which means

01:23:47.870 --> 01:23:50.950 align:middle line:84%
we operate 95% of the time
from our subconscious mind.

01:23:50.950 --> 01:23:52.490 align:middle line:90%
You say, well, how come?

01:23:52.490 --> 01:23:55.754 align:middle line:84%
And I go, remember the conscious
mind is not time bound.

01:23:55.754 --> 01:23:57.420 align:middle line:84%
I asked you what are
you doing next week

01:23:57.420 --> 01:23:58.210 align:middle line:90%
and you gave me an answer.

01:23:58.210 --> 01:23:59.839 align:middle line:84%
I say, Lisa, what
did you do last week?

01:23:59.839 --> 01:24:01.380 align:middle line:84%
And your mind goes
back to last week.

01:24:01.380 --> 01:24:03.930 align:middle line:84%
And I say, while
we're sitting here,

01:24:03.930 --> 01:24:05.240 align:middle line:90%
solve the square root of 3.

01:24:05.240 --> 01:24:07.330 align:middle line:84%
And your mind will
disconnect, go up in your head

01:24:07.330 --> 01:24:08.450 align:middle line:90%
and start solving.

01:24:08.450 --> 01:24:10.940 align:middle line:84%
And so basically it says
this, the conscious mind

01:24:10.940 --> 01:24:12.380 align:middle line:90%
is not always present.

01:24:12.380 --> 01:24:13.600 align:middle line:90%
It's thinking.

01:24:13.600 --> 01:24:16.590 align:middle line:84%
Well, it turns out it's
thinking 95% of the time.

01:24:16.590 --> 01:24:17.950 align:middle line:90%
Well, here's the problem.

01:24:17.950 --> 01:24:20.740 align:middle line:84%
If the conscious mind is engaged
in some kind of thinking,

01:24:20.740 --> 01:24:24.090 align:middle line:84%
then it's not paying
attention, and the default

01:24:24.090 --> 01:24:25.860 align:middle line:90%
is the subconscious.

01:24:25.860 --> 01:24:28.440 align:middle line:84%
So every time your conscious
mind is thinking a thought,

01:24:28.440 --> 01:24:32.200 align:middle line:84%
you then go into the
subconscious program.

01:24:32.200 --> 01:24:34.064 align:middle line:90%
So our issue is this.

01:24:34.064 --> 01:24:35.730 align:middle line:84%
How come positive
thinking doesn't work?

01:24:35.730 --> 01:24:39.650 align:middle line:84%
And I go, because you're
only using it 5% of the time.

01:24:39.650 --> 01:24:42.300 align:middle line:84%
95% of the time, you're
operating off the subconscious.

01:24:42.300 --> 01:24:43.680 align:middle line:90%
And then here's the conflict.

01:24:43.680 --> 01:24:44.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, how do you?

01:24:44.780 --> 01:24:46.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: The subconscious
is not even basically

01:24:46.780 --> 01:24:47.760 align:middle line:90%
your behavior.

01:24:47.760 --> 01:24:49.080 align:middle line:90%
You got it from other people.

01:24:49.080 --> 01:24:51.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But how do you change
that subconscious programming,

01:24:51.580 --> 01:24:52.050 align:middle line:90%
or?

01:24:52.050 --> 01:24:53.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: First, recognize it.

01:24:53.060 --> 01:24:53.455 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:24:53.455 --> 01:24:53.850 align:middle line:90%
Good start.

01:24:53.850 --> 01:24:55.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: You have to recognize
you have this subconscious

01:24:55.570 --> 01:24:56.442 align:middle line:90%
programming, OK?

01:24:56.442 --> 01:24:58.400 align:middle line:84%
And most people don't
because they still think,

01:24:58.400 --> 01:25:00.870 align:middle line:84%
oh, I'm operating my life
with my conscious creativity.

01:25:00.870 --> 01:25:02.690 align:middle line:90%
And I go, 5%.

01:25:02.690 --> 01:25:05.260 align:middle line:84%
95% you're playing these
subconscious programs you

01:25:05.260 --> 01:25:06.400 align:middle line:90%
got from your family.

01:25:06.400 --> 01:25:07.982 align:middle line:84%
And as I love to
say in the lectures

01:25:07.982 --> 01:25:09.690 align:middle line:84%
because most people
laugh because they're

01:25:09.690 --> 01:25:10.523 align:middle line:90%
so familiar with it.

01:25:10.523 --> 01:25:12.770 align:middle line:84%
I say look, you have
a very close friend.

01:25:12.770 --> 01:25:14.670 align:middle line:84%
You know your friend's
behavior, and you

01:25:14.670 --> 01:25:16.680 align:middle line:84%
happen to know your
friend's parent.

01:25:16.680 --> 01:25:20.530 align:middle line:84%
And I say, then someday
you casually recognize

01:25:20.530 --> 01:25:23.380 align:middle line:84%
that your friend shares
some of the same behavior

01:25:23.380 --> 01:25:25.910 align:middle line:84%
as their parents, so you say
your friend, hey, you know,

01:25:25.910 --> 01:25:27.990 align:middle line:90%
Bill, you're just like your dad.

01:25:27.990 --> 01:25:29.730 align:middle line:90%
And you back away from Bill.

01:25:29.730 --> 01:25:30.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And you get mad.

01:25:30.730 --> 01:25:32.605 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Because Bill's
the one that's like,

01:25:32.605 --> 01:25:34.990 align:middle line:84%
how-- how can you
compare me to my dad?

01:25:34.990 --> 01:25:36.710 align:middle line:84%
And I go, well,
there are two very

01:25:36.710 --> 01:25:38.380 align:middle line:84%
profound points from
one simple story,

01:25:38.380 --> 01:25:40.180 align:middle line:84%
and profound point
number one is this.

01:25:40.180 --> 01:25:42.969 align:middle line:84%
Everyone else can see that
Bill behaves like his dad;

01:25:42.969 --> 01:25:44.385 align:middle line:84%
it's only Bill who
doesn't see it.

01:25:44.385 --> 01:25:44.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:25:44.670 --> 01:25:45.169 align:middle line:90%
Right.

01:25:45.169 --> 01:25:46.140 align:middle line:90%
Right.

01:25:46.140 --> 01:25:47.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And this
is very profound.

01:25:47.130 --> 01:25:48.330 align:middle line:90%
Why does he behave like his dad?

01:25:48.330 --> 01:25:50.413 align:middle line:84%
Because he got the program
in the first five years

01:25:50.413 --> 01:25:51.540 align:middle line:90%
by observing his dad.

01:25:51.540 --> 01:25:53.970 align:middle line:84%
So when his mind is
not paying attention,

01:25:53.970 --> 01:25:55.810 align:middle line:90%
he plays his father's behavior.

01:25:55.810 --> 01:25:57.840 align:middle line:84%
But because his mind's
not paying attention,

01:25:57.840 --> 01:25:59.460 align:middle line:90%
he doesn't see it, OK?

01:25:59.460 --> 01:26:00.839 align:middle line:90%
And profound point number two.

01:26:00.839 --> 01:26:03.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: OK, because I want to--
yeah, how do you change this?

01:26:03.380 --> 01:26:03.910 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:26:03.910 --> 01:26:04.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: I'm going
to get to that.

01:26:04.470 --> 01:26:04.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:26:04.970 --> 01:26:05.500 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:26:05.500 --> 01:26:06.915 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Profound point
number two is we are all Bill,

01:26:06.915 --> 01:26:08.590 align:middle line:90%
and that's what we have to own.

01:26:08.590 --> 01:26:11.206 align:middle line:84%
95% of our behavior
is invisible to us.

01:26:11.206 --> 01:26:13.080 align:middle line:84%
And most of that behavior
has been programmed

01:26:13.080 --> 01:26:15.350 align:middle line:84%
by other people, and
it has their beliefs

01:26:15.350 --> 01:26:18.920 align:middle line:84%
or wishes not ours, or
their way of life, not ours.

01:26:18.920 --> 01:26:21.440 align:middle line:84%
And so it turns out,
are we living the lives

01:26:21.440 --> 01:26:22.460 align:middle line:90%
that we really want?

01:26:22.460 --> 01:26:24.170 align:middle line:84%
Or are we living
the lives that we've

01:26:24.170 --> 01:26:26.367 align:middle line:90%
been programmed to live, OK?

01:26:26.367 --> 01:26:27.950 align:middle line:84%
And how important
is this programming?

01:26:27.950 --> 01:26:31.440 align:middle line:84%
This is a very important fact
that people have to gather.

01:26:31.440 --> 01:26:34.730 align:middle line:84%
When a child is adopted
into a family that

01:26:34.730 --> 01:26:38.890 align:middle line:84%
has a lineage of cancer,
the adopted child

01:26:38.890 --> 01:26:42.180 align:middle line:84%
will get the family cancer
with the same propensity

01:26:42.180 --> 01:26:43.562 align:middle line:90%
as any of the natural siblings.

01:26:43.562 --> 01:26:44.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You're kidding.

01:26:44.520 --> 01:26:45.410 align:middle line:90%
Without the--

01:26:45.410 --> 01:26:47.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Without the genetics.

01:26:47.240 --> 01:26:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And what it turned out is,
as I said, 90% of cancer

01:26:50.580 --> 01:26:52.430 align:middle line:90%
is lifestyle.

01:26:52.430 --> 01:26:55.164 align:middle line:84%
90% of cancers, how do you
learn to respond to the world?

01:26:55.164 --> 01:26:57.080 align:middle line:84%
I say, well, you learn
this from your parents,

01:26:57.080 --> 01:26:59.700 align:middle line:84%
whether you're adopted
or you're genetic family,

01:26:59.700 --> 01:27:01.790 align:middle line:84%
it's still you're learning
the same behavior.

01:27:01.790 --> 01:27:02.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:27:02.290 --> 01:27:04.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: So the
cancer is expressed

01:27:04.260 --> 01:27:06.170 align:middle line:84%
in the adopted
child just the same.

01:27:06.170 --> 01:27:06.670 align:middle line:90%
Again--

01:27:06.670 --> 01:27:07.005 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Amazing.

01:27:07.005 --> 01:27:08.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: -important point.

01:27:08.130 --> 01:27:10.470 align:middle line:84%
It's not in your genes;
it's in your response

01:27:10.470 --> 01:27:11.870 align:middle line:90%
to the environment.

01:27:11.870 --> 01:27:13.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Response to
the environment, yes.

01:27:13.790 --> 01:27:14.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: So now--

01:27:14.540 --> 01:27:16.916 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: OK, so then-- all
right, so how do you change it?

01:27:16.916 --> 01:27:18.706 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to ask you,
how do you change it?

01:27:18.706 --> 01:27:20.260 align:middle line:84%
What do you do with
this information?

01:27:20.260 --> 01:27:23.600 align:middle line:84%
How do we know and how we move
forward with this information?

01:27:23.600 --> 01:27:24.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: OK.

01:27:24.950 --> 01:27:27.230 align:middle line:90%
Well, let's put it this way.

01:27:27.230 --> 01:27:30.140 align:middle line:84%
What if you-- first
question is this,

01:27:30.140 --> 01:27:32.580 align:middle line:84%
what-- eliminate the
subconscious for a minute

01:27:32.580 --> 01:27:35.032 align:middle line:84%
and just say, if
you could live just

01:27:35.032 --> 01:27:36.990 align:middle line:84%
from your conscious mind,
which has your wishes

01:27:36.990 --> 01:27:39.620 align:middle line:84%
and desires and aspirations,
what would your life be like?

01:27:39.620 --> 01:27:41.210 align:middle line:84%
And now I'm going
to say, most people

01:27:41.210 --> 01:27:42.876 align:middle line:84%
have done this in a
period of their life

01:27:42.876 --> 01:27:44.804 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't
realize it, but they'll

01:27:44.804 --> 01:27:46.220 align:middle line:84%
know the period
I'm talking about.

01:27:46.220 --> 01:27:48.972 align:middle line:84%
And that is, when you fall
deeply in love with somebody.

01:27:48.972 --> 01:27:50.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, everyone
remembers that, yes.

01:27:50.680 --> 01:27:51.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: OK.

01:27:51.800 --> 01:27:53.290 align:middle line:90%
I call it the honeymoon effect.

01:27:53.290 --> 01:27:54.360 align:middle line:84%
And I say, what is
the honeymoon effect?

01:27:54.360 --> 01:27:56.901 align:middle line:84%
And I say, well, go back to that
time you fell deeply in love

01:27:56.901 --> 01:27:57.520 align:middle line:90%
with somebody.

01:27:57.520 --> 01:27:58.740 align:middle line:90%
And I say, were you healthy?

01:27:58.740 --> 01:28:01.325 align:middle line:84%
And almost everybody says oh,
I was exuberantly healthy.

01:28:01.325 --> 01:28:02.450 align:middle line:90%
I say, did you have energy?

01:28:02.450 --> 01:28:05.660 align:middle line:84%
And they say, of course, we
had an abundance of energy.

01:28:05.660 --> 01:28:09.930 align:middle line:84%
And I go, was life so beautiful
when you were in the honeymoon

01:28:09.930 --> 01:28:10.892 align:middle line:90%
that--

01:28:10.892 --> 01:28:12.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Rose-colored glasses.

01:28:12.100 --> 01:28:13.391 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Rose-colored glasses.

01:28:13.391 --> 01:28:15.070 align:middle line:84%
Life was heaven on
Earth, wasn't it?

01:28:15.070 --> 01:28:18.220 align:middle line:84%
And I go, that was
not an accident.

01:28:18.220 --> 01:28:20.120 align:middle line:90%
That was a creation.

01:28:20.120 --> 01:28:22.720 align:middle line:84%
Because science has now
recognized the unique fact

01:28:22.720 --> 01:28:25.980 align:middle line:84%
when you fell in love
like that, you absolutely

01:28:25.980 --> 01:28:28.640 align:middle line:84%
operated almost primarily
from the conscious mind

01:28:28.640 --> 01:28:31.059 align:middle line:84%
and did not go into
the default program.

01:28:31.059 --> 01:28:32.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In that
short period of time,

01:28:32.600 --> 01:28:34.470 align:middle line:84%
you're operating from
the conscious mind.

01:28:34.470 --> 01:28:36.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And it's
also-- another term

01:28:36.800 --> 01:28:39.440 align:middle line:84%
is like being mindful,
or Buddhist mindfulness.

01:28:39.440 --> 01:28:40.340 align:middle line:90%
It's the same idea.

01:28:40.340 --> 01:28:40.920 align:middle line:90%
It says what?

01:28:40.920 --> 01:28:43.350 align:middle line:84%
If I don't know operate from
the subconscious programs

01:28:43.350 --> 01:28:45.770 align:middle line:84%
with its limiting beliefs
that were acquired

01:28:45.770 --> 01:28:47.660 align:middle line:84%
and I'm operating only
from the mind that

01:28:47.660 --> 01:28:49.610 align:middle line:84%
has wishes and desires
and aspirations,

01:28:49.610 --> 01:28:52.030 align:middle line:84%
then every decision
and every action

01:28:52.030 --> 01:28:56.060 align:middle line:84%
is done with my wish and
my desire attached to it.

01:28:56.060 --> 01:28:57.492 align:middle line:84%
OK, when two people
come together

01:28:57.492 --> 01:28:59.200 align:middle line:84%
and they're both in
the honeymoon effect,

01:28:59.200 --> 01:29:01.445 align:middle line:84%
then they're both creating
from their conscious minds

01:29:01.445 --> 01:29:02.820 align:middle line:84%
and this is called
the honeymoon.

01:29:02.820 --> 01:29:04.180 align:middle line:90%
And now you might then say--

01:29:04.180 --> 01:29:05.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, how
come it doesn't last?

01:29:05.450 --> 01:29:06.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: How come
it doesn't last?

01:29:06.290 --> 01:29:08.164 align:middle line:84%
And that's a perfect
question for this reason

01:29:08.164 --> 01:29:09.530 align:middle line:90%
is why doesn't it last?

01:29:09.530 --> 01:29:10.570 align:middle line:90%
And the answer is this.

01:29:10.570 --> 01:29:13.270 align:middle line:84%
Because at some
point life gets busy.

01:29:13.270 --> 01:29:16.259 align:middle line:84%
You still have to pay the rent,
you still got to fix the car.

01:29:16.259 --> 01:29:18.300 align:middle line:84%
You still have to do these
things, so what is it?

01:29:18.300 --> 01:29:21.390 align:middle line:84%
Your mind starts to think about
oh, what am I going to do?

01:29:21.390 --> 01:29:22.330 align:middle line:90%
What's my schedule?

01:29:22.330 --> 01:29:23.163 align:middle line:90%
What's on my agenda?

01:29:23.163 --> 01:29:24.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Enter in stress.

01:29:24.290 --> 01:29:26.039 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And stress
and all these things.

01:29:26.039 --> 01:29:28.529 align:middle line:84%
So now let's say
you and I are having

01:29:28.529 --> 01:29:31.070 align:middle line:84%
this wonderful relationship and
we're in the honeymoon thing,

01:29:31.070 --> 01:29:33.880 align:middle line:84%
and I'm thinking
about all of a sudden,

01:29:33.880 --> 01:29:35.054 align:middle line:90%
oh, I got to pay the rent.

01:29:35.054 --> 01:29:36.220 align:middle line:90%
How am I'm going to do this?

01:29:36.220 --> 01:29:38.390 align:middle line:84%
And you come up and you
ask me some simple question

01:29:38.390 --> 01:29:40.891 align:middle line:84%
and I'm in this state, and I
turn around and go, Lisa, blah,

01:29:40.891 --> 01:29:42.340 align:middle line:90%
blah, blah, blah.

01:29:42.340 --> 01:29:45.960 align:middle line:84%
And you look at me and
you go, who are you?

01:29:45.960 --> 01:29:47.515 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Where's the
honeymoon effect?

01:29:47.515 --> 01:29:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Where's
the honeymoon now?

01:29:48.860 --> 01:29:50.901 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is, what
happened, and here's what

01:29:50.901 --> 01:29:51.580 align:middle line:90%
happened.

01:29:51.580 --> 01:29:53.850 align:middle line:84%
Up to now, we were
both operating

01:29:53.850 --> 01:29:55.956 align:middle line:84%
from our conscious
wishes and desires.

01:29:55.956 --> 01:29:57.830 align:middle line:84%
At that moment when you
ask me that question,

01:29:57.830 --> 01:30:00.100 align:middle line:84%
my conscious mind was
busy, so what do I do?

01:30:00.100 --> 01:30:01.690 align:middle line:90%
Default, subconscious.

01:30:01.690 --> 01:30:03.090 align:middle line:90%
Whose behavior is in there?

01:30:03.090 --> 01:30:03.667 align:middle line:90%
My father's.

01:30:03.667 --> 01:30:04.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Your programming--

01:30:04.750 --> 01:30:06.166 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And all
of a sudden, you

01:30:06.166 --> 01:30:08.590 align:middle line:84%
see this behavior that
was my father's, right?

01:30:08.590 --> 01:30:11.089 align:middle line:84%
And it came out and you
looked at me and said, look,

01:30:11.089 --> 01:30:13.130 align:middle line:84%
I've been with you for
this whole period of time.

01:30:13.130 --> 01:30:14.120 align:middle line:90%
I never saw this.

01:30:14.120 --> 01:30:15.946 align:middle line:90%
Who are you with that behavior?

01:30:15.946 --> 01:30:18.320 align:middle line:84%
And here's where the problem
comes in in the relationship

01:30:18.320 --> 01:30:22.310 align:middle line:84%
because, as I mentioned before,
did I even see what I said?

01:30:22.310 --> 01:30:25.640 align:middle line:84%
No, because I was coming
from my subconscious mind.

01:30:25.640 --> 01:30:27.940 align:middle line:84%
So all of a sudden
you say, who are you?

01:30:27.940 --> 01:30:31.590 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden I feel,
what do you mean who am I?

01:30:31.590 --> 01:30:32.740 align:middle line:90%
I've always been this way?

01:30:32.740 --> 01:30:33.323 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:30:33.323 --> 01:30:33.970 align:middle line:90%
Right.

01:30:33.970 --> 01:30:35.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And it's like,
well, that's absolutely true,

01:30:35.110 --> 01:30:37.790 align:middle line:84%
but I never-- I didn't see
what I just said either.

01:30:37.790 --> 01:30:40.331 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This could explain why
the divorce rate is so high.

01:30:40.331 --> 01:30:41.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Exactly.

01:30:41.080 --> 01:30:44.060 align:middle line:84%
Because what happens is as
the relationship continues,

01:30:44.060 --> 01:30:47.710 align:middle line:84%
as life gets involved and more
and more of these subconscious

01:30:47.710 --> 01:30:50.700 align:middle line:84%
programs start showing up, they
were not part of the honeymoon.

01:30:50.700 --> 01:30:52.200 align:middle line:84%
If they started
off on day one, you

01:30:52.200 --> 01:30:54.620 align:middle line:90%
may have not gotten to day two.

01:30:54.620 --> 01:30:57.100 align:middle line:84%
But you did the honeymoon,
but now these show up

01:30:57.100 --> 01:30:58.605 align:middle line:84%
and now you're in
a funny position.

01:30:58.605 --> 01:31:01.120 align:middle line:84%
It's like, I really
love the honeymoon part.

01:31:01.120 --> 01:31:03.460 align:middle line:84%
These new behaviors I'm
not really happy with,

01:31:03.460 --> 01:31:05.460 align:middle line:90%
but I'll compromise.

01:31:05.460 --> 01:31:07.389 align:middle line:84%
OK, I'll accept
those lousy behaviors

01:31:07.389 --> 01:31:09.180 align:middle line:84%
because I really love
this honeymoon stuff.

01:31:09.180 --> 01:31:09.763 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:31:09.763 --> 01:31:10.830 align:middle line:90%
Because I want that back.

01:31:10.830 --> 01:31:11.480 align:middle line:90%
Because I want the honeymoon.

01:31:11.480 --> 01:31:12.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And yet, the
glow of the honeymoon

01:31:12.730 --> 01:31:15.140 align:middle line:84%
starts to disappear now
we have life again here.

01:31:15.140 --> 01:31:16.320 align:middle line:90%
But the question is this.

01:31:16.320 --> 01:31:19.060 align:middle line:84%
But if a lot of these behaviors
show up and a lot of them

01:31:19.060 --> 01:31:22.430 align:middle line:84%
may be not even something
you want to compromise with,

01:31:22.430 --> 01:31:26.130 align:middle line:84%
that then ultimately
went from honeymoon

01:31:26.130 --> 01:31:29.710 align:middle line:90%
to compromise to separation.

01:31:29.710 --> 01:31:32.810 align:middle line:84%
And that's a result of I can't
compromise that much anymore.

01:31:32.810 --> 01:31:36.200 align:middle line:84%
So now, finally,
what would happen

01:31:36.200 --> 01:31:39.070 align:middle line:90%
if you could reprogram the mind?

01:31:39.070 --> 01:31:41.300 align:middle line:84%
What if you could
reprogram that subconscious

01:31:41.300 --> 01:31:43.880 align:middle line:84%
so that it had the exact
same beliefs of your wishes

01:31:43.880 --> 01:31:45.160 align:middle line:90%
and desires?

01:31:45.160 --> 01:31:47.870 align:middle line:84%
The significance on a
piece of paper is simple.

01:31:47.870 --> 01:31:50.090 align:middle line:84%
That means if your
mind starts to wander

01:31:50.090 --> 01:31:52.230 align:middle line:84%
and you kick into
the subconscious,

01:31:52.230 --> 01:31:54.160 align:middle line:84%
you'll still be playing
the same behaviors

01:31:54.160 --> 01:31:55.770 align:middle line:90%
that you used in the honeymoon.

01:31:55.770 --> 01:31:57.000 align:middle line:90%
Guess what?

01:31:57.000 --> 01:31:58.680 align:middle line:90%
Perpetual honeymoon.

01:31:58.680 --> 01:32:01.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you can control
this with the conscious mind.

01:32:01.970 --> 01:32:04.680 align:middle line:84%
And to wrap all of this up
and all of this together,

01:32:04.680 --> 01:32:06.900 align:middle line:84%
this is how you change
the environment back

01:32:06.900 --> 01:32:09.120 align:middle line:84%
to the healthy environment
in the Petri dish

01:32:09.120 --> 01:32:10.300 align:middle line:90%
is with the conscious mind.

01:32:10.300 --> 01:32:12.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely,
because the conscious mind

01:32:12.300 --> 01:32:13.937 align:middle line:84%
is the one that
puts the chemistry

01:32:13.937 --> 01:32:15.770 align:middle line:84%
and that fits what you
want out of life, not

01:32:15.770 --> 01:32:17.340 align:middle line:90%
the program that you received.

01:32:17.340 --> 01:32:19.079 align:middle line:84%
Now if I can create
heaven on Earth

01:32:19.079 --> 01:32:20.620 align:middle line:84%
and you could create
heaven on Earth,

01:32:20.620 --> 01:32:22.870 align:middle line:84%
then I start to realize that
my neighbors are creating

01:32:22.870 --> 01:32:25.080 align:middle line:84%
heaven on Earth,
and these people.

01:32:25.080 --> 01:32:27.530 align:middle line:84%
At some point, you
realize, well, Earth

01:32:27.530 --> 01:32:30.014 align:middle line:84%
could be heaven if everybody
just put in their own,

01:32:30.014 --> 01:32:31.430 align:middle line:84%
you know, their
wishes and desires

01:32:31.430 --> 01:32:33.240 align:middle line:84%
and got rid of the
bad programming that's

01:32:33.240 --> 01:32:35.440 align:middle line:84%
been passed from
generation to generation.

01:32:35.440 --> 01:32:37.190 align:middle line:84%
It didn't just come
from my parents.

01:32:37.190 --> 01:32:38.690 align:middle line:84%
My parents had
parents who gave them

01:32:38.690 --> 01:32:41.387 align:middle line:84%
the belief that they
passed on to me.

01:32:41.387 --> 01:32:42.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This is-- exactly.

01:32:42.470 --> 01:32:44.860 align:middle line:84%
This is what it means to
change the environment,

01:32:44.860 --> 01:32:46.630 align:middle line:84%
your perception of
the environment.

01:32:46.630 --> 01:32:48.800 align:middle line:84%
And if critical
mass can do that,

01:32:48.800 --> 01:32:51.846 align:middle line:84%
this is how you create
spontaneous evolution.

01:32:51.846 --> 01:32:52.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely.

01:32:52.720 --> 01:32:52.975 align:middle line:90%
And that's--

01:32:52.975 --> 01:32:53.605 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Which is the
name of your book.

01:32:53.605 --> 01:32:55.188 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: -why I get
so excited about,

01:32:55.188 --> 01:32:57.672 align:middle line:84%
look, if we had knowledge
that was incorrect

01:32:57.672 --> 01:32:59.130 align:middle line:84%
and we operate from
that knowledge,

01:32:59.130 --> 01:33:01.805 align:middle line:84%
then by definition, a lack of
knowledge is a lack of power.

01:33:01.805 --> 01:33:04.180 align:middle line:84%
If we get this new information
out to the public and say,

01:33:04.180 --> 01:33:05.440 align:middle line:90%
you're not a victim.

01:33:05.440 --> 01:33:07.230 align:middle line:90%
You're a powerful person.

01:33:07.230 --> 01:33:08.980 align:middle line:84%
You could drink
strychnine if you want to.

01:33:08.980 --> 01:33:09.970 align:middle line:84%
Not that I'm
interested in doing it.

01:33:09.970 --> 01:33:11.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I don't suggest that.

01:33:11.340 --> 01:33:13.631 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: But the fact is,
you can do all these things.

01:33:13.631 --> 01:33:15.990 align:middle line:84%
And the issue then
says, we're not

01:33:15.990 --> 01:33:18.990 align:middle line:84%
dependent on other
people for our happiness,

01:33:18.990 --> 01:33:21.575 align:middle line:84%
we just have to look at
what's been conflicting.

01:33:21.575 --> 01:33:24.290 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out, it's
not your conscious mind

01:33:24.290 --> 01:33:25.610 align:middle line:90%
that's conflicting.

01:33:25.610 --> 01:33:27.790 align:middle line:84%
The conscious mind has all
that positive thinking.

01:33:27.790 --> 01:33:31.700 align:middle line:84%
But the default mind
takes 95% of the show.

01:33:31.700 --> 01:33:33.522 align:middle line:90%
If you become aware of it--

01:33:33.522 --> 01:33:34.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And change
your perception.

01:33:34.980 --> 01:33:37.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: -change, you
can change these beliefs.

01:33:37.720 --> 01:33:40.632 align:middle line:84%
And the issue about changing
beliefs, very quickly, is

01:33:40.632 --> 01:33:42.090 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people
say, well, I'm just

01:33:42.090 --> 01:33:43.950 align:middle line:84%
going to give myself
a good talking to.

01:33:43.950 --> 01:33:46.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to say,
you know, Bruce,

01:33:46.260 --> 01:33:48.780 align:middle line:84%
you're trying to take
care of your weight here

01:33:48.780 --> 01:33:50.940 align:middle line:84%
and you have this
donut in your hand.

01:33:50.940 --> 01:33:53.230 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, what are
you doing with that donut?

01:33:53.230 --> 01:33:54.120 align:middle line:84%
And then you get
mad at yourself.

01:33:54.120 --> 01:33:55.820 align:middle line:84%
What are you doing with this
stupid donut, you know, blah,

01:33:55.820 --> 01:33:56.190 align:middle line:90%
blah, blah.

01:33:56.190 --> 01:33:57.790 align:middle line:84%
And you get mad at yourself
and you're talking to yourself,

01:33:57.790 --> 01:33:58.998 align:middle line:90%
don't do that, don't do that.

01:33:58.998 --> 01:34:01.180 align:middle line:84%
And I say, who are
you talking to?

01:34:01.180 --> 01:34:03.470 align:middle line:84%
And the issue is, well, I'm
talking to my subconscious

01:34:03.470 --> 01:34:03.860 align:middle line:90%
mind.

01:34:03.860 --> 01:34:05.900 align:middle line:84%
I go, well, that's where
the problem comes from.

01:34:05.900 --> 01:34:07.740 align:middle line:84%
There's nobody in the
subconscious mind.

01:34:07.740 --> 01:34:09.190 align:middle line:90%
It's a machine, it's a recorder.

01:34:09.190 --> 01:34:11.850 align:middle line:84%
I say you have a tape recorder,
it's playing a program,

01:34:11.850 --> 01:34:13.600 align:middle line:84%
and I say go up and
talk to it and tell me

01:34:13.600 --> 01:34:15.250 align:middle line:90%
when the program changes.

01:34:15.250 --> 01:34:17.400 align:middle line:90%
The answer is it won't change.

01:34:17.400 --> 01:34:17.900 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't--

01:34:17.900 --> 01:34:19.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how do you
put the donut down?

01:34:19.730 --> 01:34:21.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, you have
to push the record button

01:34:21.050 --> 01:34:22.883 align:middle line:84%
and put a new program
into the subconscious.

01:34:22.883 --> 01:34:24.891 align:middle line:90%
There's a record process, OK?

01:34:24.891 --> 01:34:27.140 align:middle line:84%
And I say, well, how does
the subconscious mind learn?

01:34:27.140 --> 01:34:28.840 align:middle line:84%
Not the way the
conscious mind learns.

01:34:28.840 --> 01:34:31.490 align:middle line:84%
Conscious mind, creative,
read a self-help book.

01:34:31.490 --> 01:34:33.560 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the book
I say, here's a quiz.

01:34:33.560 --> 01:34:34.840 align:middle line:84%
Did you really learn
what was in the book?

01:34:34.840 --> 01:34:36.050 align:middle line:90%
You say, yeah, I got 100.

01:34:36.050 --> 01:34:36.940 align:middle line:90%
I say, great.

01:34:36.940 --> 01:34:38.900 align:middle line:84%
You really know about
this self-help book.

01:34:38.900 --> 01:34:40.110 align:middle line:90%
Did your life change?

01:34:40.110 --> 01:34:41.170 align:middle line:90%
No.

01:34:41.170 --> 01:34:42.400 align:middle line:90%
And I go, why?

01:34:42.400 --> 01:34:44.240 align:middle line:84%
Because you educated
your conscious mind.

01:34:44.240 --> 01:34:46.540 align:middle line:84%
The subconscious
mind learns primarily

01:34:46.540 --> 01:34:50.520 align:middle line:84%
from habit or hypnosis, like it
learned in the first six years

01:34:50.520 --> 01:34:51.210 align:middle line:90%
is hypnosis.

01:34:51.210 --> 01:34:53.400 align:middle line:84%
After that, how did
you learn something?

01:34:53.400 --> 01:34:55.870 align:middle line:84%
You repeated it and you
repeated it and you repeated it.

01:34:55.870 --> 01:34:58.150 align:middle line:84%
That's how the
subconscious mind learns.

01:34:58.150 --> 01:35:01.690 align:middle line:84%
So reading a self-help book does
not change the subconscious.

01:35:01.690 --> 01:35:04.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But what does is
making the conscious decisions

01:35:04.780 --> 01:35:05.405 align:middle line:90%
and repeating--

01:35:05.405 --> 01:35:06.488 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: To make a habit.

01:35:06.488 --> 01:35:07.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: -habitually, yes.

01:35:07.740 --> 01:35:08.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Make a
habit out something.

01:35:08.830 --> 01:35:10.038 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a great point.

01:35:10.038 --> 01:35:12.760 align:middle line:84%
And that-- it's beautiful how
you tied all of this together,

01:35:12.760 --> 01:35:17.330 align:middle line:84%
how you took the concept of
our positive thoughts really do

01:35:17.330 --> 01:35:20.910 align:middle line:84%
impact the genes and move
us towards a place of growth

01:35:20.910 --> 01:35:23.360 align:middle line:84%
and the cells towards
a place of growth.

01:35:23.360 --> 01:35:26.860 align:middle line:84%
